1
00:00:59,911 --> 00:01:02,412
[WHEEZING]

2
00:01:02,414 --> 00:01:04,064
[MATCH STRIKES]

3
00:01:07,502 --> 00:01:09,519
[WHEEZING CONTINUES]

4
00:01:17,645 --> 00:01:21,415
[SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

5
00:01:21,417 --> 00:01:23,884
[HORSES GALLOPING IN DISTANCE]

6
00:01:26,870 --> 00:01:30,173
[DOGS BARKING]

7
00:01:33,895 --> 00:01:36,045
[GUNS COCK]

8
00:01:38,415 --> 00:01:40,050
WOMAN [WHISPERING]:
Dan...

9
00:01:44,588 --> 00:01:46,355
Maybe it's the wind.
[MAN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

10
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:49,826
[CATTLE MOOING]

11
00:01:53,765 --> 00:01:55,832
[HORSES NEIGHING]

12
00:01:55,834 --> 00:01:57,067
No!

13
00:02:01,105 --> 00:02:02,405
Stop!

14
00:02:02,407 --> 00:02:04,507
Please! Stop!

15
00:02:04,509 --> 00:02:06,009
[GRUNTS]

16
00:02:06,011 --> 00:02:07,377
MAN: 
Tucker!

17
00:02:10,715 --> 00:02:14,017
You have a week, Evans.
Then we burn the house.

18
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,788
William?

19
00:02:18,790 --> 00:02:20,891
Hey! William!

20
00:02:20,893 --> 00:02:22,926
[HORSES NEIGHING]

21
00:02:24,829 --> 00:02:26,362
Out. Out!

22
00:02:30,267 --> 00:02:31,234
William!

23
00:02:39,627 --> 00:02:42,729
God damn it,
William! William!

24
00:02:43,964 --> 00:02:46,116
Goddamn it!
Put that down!

25
00:02:46,118 --> 00:02:47,918
Come here!
Let go!

26
00:02:47,920 --> 00:02:48,869
Let go!

27
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:55,392
It's the last feed we got!

28
00:03:00,865 --> 00:03:02,265
[CATTLE MOOING]

29
00:03:10,474 --> 00:03:12,408
[MEN SHOUTING IN DISTANCE]

30
00:03:14,211 --> 00:03:16,412
I'll take care of this.

31
00:03:20,284 --> 00:03:21,551
No, you won't.

32
00:03:54,084 --> 00:03:56,219
Herd's over the ridge
by now.

33
00:03:56,221 --> 00:03:58,988
You go get cleaned up.

34
00:04:04,928 --> 00:04:06,196
[SIGHS]

35
00:04:08,899 --> 00:04:10,266
You lied to me, Dan.

36
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:15,137
You told me we made
payments to Hollander.

37
00:04:15,139 --> 00:04:17,940
We did...some.

38
00:04:17,942 --> 00:04:20,543
How do you think
we bought feed, Alice?

39
00:04:20,545 --> 00:04:22,045
Three months water?

40
00:04:22,047 --> 00:04:24,948
Medicine for Mark?

41
00:04:24,950 --> 00:04:28,267
I had a choice between our
family and paying it down.

42
00:04:28,269 --> 00:04:30,537
We're supposed to make
decisions together.

43
00:04:30,539 --> 00:04:32,772
Would you have made it
any different?

44
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:40,580
Alice, we can't
make it rain together.

45
00:04:40,582 --> 00:04:44,150
Or turn the dust
into grass.

46
00:04:44,152 --> 00:04:46,653
Can't stop Hollander from selling
our land to the railroad, either.

47
00:04:51,308 --> 00:04:55,311
It's too bad the doctors at
Essex saved so much of my leg.

48
00:04:55,313 --> 00:04:57,714
I read that the pension act
pays by the pound now.

49
00:04:57,716 --> 00:04:59,282
[CHUCKLES]

50
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,202
Stop looking at me like that.

51
00:05:03,204 --> 00:05:05,705
You gonna tell the marshal
what those men did?

52
00:05:05,707 --> 00:05:07,507
WILLIAM:
Marshal ain't doing shit.

53
00:05:07,509 --> 00:05:10,477
William.
First thing, Mark,

54
00:05:10,479 --> 00:05:13,496
I'm gonna take you boys, and
we're gonna round up the herd,

55
00:05:13,498 --> 00:05:15,832
and then I'm goin' into town.
What are you gonna do in town?

56
00:05:15,834 --> 00:05:19,352
I'm gonna tell Hollander
to make this right.

57
00:05:19,354 --> 00:05:21,437
I'm gonna tell him...

58
00:05:21,439 --> 00:05:22,772
to pay for a new barn.

59
00:05:24,508 --> 00:05:26,876
Maybe we should just shoot
him like Will says.

60
00:05:56,974 --> 00:05:58,541
Coach is headed
for Bisbee, Boss.

61
00:06:00,278 --> 00:06:02,312
Girded with iron,
Pinks on top,

62
00:06:02,314 --> 00:06:04,581
double shotguns,

63
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,465
and a Gatling.

64
00:06:06,467 --> 00:06:09,135
[CLICKS TONGUE]

65
00:06:28,355 --> 00:06:30,173
[MEN CHATTERING]

66
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:49,709
[HORSE WHINNIES]

67
00:06:54,347 --> 00:06:56,716
[HORSE GRUNTS]
You shoulda let me save the feed.

68
00:06:57,601 --> 00:07:00,069
[COW MOOING]

69
00:07:00,071 --> 00:07:02,805
You gonna hock that?

70
00:07:02,807 --> 00:07:05,659
Someday, William...

71
00:07:05,661 --> 00:07:08,244
you walk in my shoes,
you might understand.

72
00:07:08,246 --> 00:07:11,447
I ain't ever walking
in your shoes.

73
00:07:11,449 --> 00:07:13,850
MARK:
Tracks over here.

74
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:21,891
[COW MOANS]

75
00:08:23,287 --> 00:08:26,022
[GUNSHOTS]

76
00:08:27,191 --> 00:08:28,358
Here we go.

77
00:08:30,093 --> 00:08:32,895
Kenny, here we go.
Here they come.

78
00:08:32,897 --> 00:08:34,029
[GUNSHOTS]

79
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:40,636
Yah!

80
00:08:40,638 --> 00:08:41,838
Yah!

81
00:08:46,643 --> 00:08:47,676
Yah!

82
00:09:03,677 --> 00:09:05,978
Pull that way!

83
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:07,363
Now that one!

84
00:09:28,602 --> 00:09:31,404
[MEN SHOUTING]

85
00:09:39,629 --> 00:09:42,131
Use the gun.
Don't let 'em get it.

86
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:53,660
Aah!

87
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:01,684
Mark, stay near.

88
00:10:01,686 --> 00:10:02,751
Mark!

89
00:10:05,522 --> 00:10:07,457
Yah! Yah!

90
00:10:09,126 --> 00:10:09,742
Goddamn!
Giddyap!

91
00:10:19,987 --> 00:10:21,487
Yah!
Get down. Now!

92
00:10:21,489 --> 00:10:22,839
Look out!
Here I come!

93
00:10:29,246 --> 00:10:31,330
[GATLING GUN FIRING]

94
00:10:37,254 --> 00:10:38,887
[MOOING]

95
00:10:42,726 --> 00:10:45,244
Yah! Yah!
Knock on 'em, Nonnie. Knock on 'em.

96
00:10:45,246 --> 00:10:46,179
Keep 'em goin'.

97
00:10:56,706 --> 00:10:59,025
Pull up. Pull up.

98
00:10:59,027 --> 00:11:00,827
Pull up!

99
00:11:49,393 --> 00:11:51,327
[COCKS GUN]
[SHELLS CLATTER]

100
00:11:55,532 --> 00:11:57,617
Morning, Pinkerton.

101
00:11:59,587 --> 00:12:01,387
Name's Charlie Prince.

102
00:12:01,389 --> 00:12:03,005
I expect you heard
of me.

103
00:12:03,007 --> 00:12:04,072
[GRUNTS]

104
00:12:06,510 --> 00:12:08,076
Well, I heard of a...

105
00:12:08,078 --> 00:12:10,245
balled-up whore named...

106
00:12:10,247 --> 00:12:13,048
Charlie Princess.

107
00:12:13,050 --> 00:12:15,301
That you, missy?

108
00:12:15,303 --> 00:12:16,385
[GRUNTS]

109
00:12:20,574 --> 00:12:22,274
I hate Pinkertons.

110
00:12:22,276 --> 00:12:23,792
Byron McElroy.

111
00:12:25,779 --> 00:12:27,580
When did your hair
turn all gray, Byron?

112
00:12:27,582 --> 00:12:29,048
[COUGHS]

113
00:12:29,050 --> 00:12:31,367
Go to hell, Ben Wade.

114
00:12:34,838 --> 00:12:36,439
Well, would you look
at all this?

115
00:12:36,441 --> 00:12:38,907
Y'all spared no expense
this time, Byron.

116
00:12:40,777 --> 00:12:42,411
I gotta say, though,
it's probably cheaper

117
00:12:42,413 --> 00:12:44,630
just to let me rob
the damn thing.

118
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:52,622
If you're gonna kill me,

119
00:12:52,624 --> 00:12:54,023
just as soon get to it.

120
00:12:56,877 --> 00:12:59,045
I ain't gonna kill you.

121
00:12:59,047 --> 00:12:59,929
Not like this.

122
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:05,451
Won't change a thing,
lettin' me live.

123
00:13:07,738 --> 00:13:09,322
I'll come for you.

124
00:13:09,324 --> 00:13:10,906
[COUGHING]

125
00:13:10,908 --> 00:13:13,142
I'd be disappointed
if you didn't.

126
00:13:13,144 --> 00:13:14,393
[HORSE NEIGHS]

127
00:13:14,395 --> 00:13:15,712
MAN: She's lit!
[FUSE CRACKLING]

128
00:13:15,714 --> 00:13:16,996
MAN #2: 
She's lit!

129
00:13:28,759 --> 00:13:29,992
[WHISTLES]

130
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,038
All right, boys.

131
00:14:04,595 --> 00:14:07,163
There you go.
It's full.

132
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:27,049
All right,
there you go.

133
00:14:27,051 --> 00:14:29,218
Come on, give me one.
One more.

134
00:14:33,089 --> 00:14:34,791
I'll ask you
to put down the money.

135
00:14:34,793 --> 00:14:36,809
You step back!
You men step back!

136
00:14:36,811 --> 00:14:39,445
All of you step back right
now, or this man dies!

137
00:14:39,447 --> 00:14:41,480
Not a smart move,
friend.

138
00:14:51,308 --> 00:14:52,274
Shit.

139
00:14:58,281 --> 00:14:59,982
He's fast.

140
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:12,644
Well, Tommy...

141
00:15:12,646 --> 00:15:15,147
it seems that
there was a Pinkerton...

142
00:15:15,149 --> 00:15:17,516
inside that coach
that wasn't quite dead yet.

143
00:15:19,286 --> 00:15:22,622
Now, I know Charlie
told you, because...

144
00:15:22,624 --> 00:15:26,292
we done got but a few rules
in this outfit.

145
00:15:26,294 --> 00:15:28,928
And this is what happens
when you put us all at risk.

146
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:37,954
Mark, look at me.
Look at me.

147
00:15:37,956 --> 00:15:39,555
Keep lookin' at me.
Back up quietly.

148
00:15:39,557 --> 00:15:41,023
Back-- William!

149
00:15:41,025 --> 00:15:43,592
William, look at me.
Back up.

150
00:15:43,594 --> 00:15:45,211
[ROCKS FALLING]
William, look at me.

151
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,047
[WHISTLES]

152
00:15:53,236 --> 00:15:54,236
[CLICKS TONGUE]

153
00:16:08,085 --> 00:16:09,185
Morning.

154
00:16:12,689 --> 00:16:14,590
Those are my cattle.

155
00:16:14,592 --> 00:16:15,691
I want 'em back.

156
00:16:15,693 --> 00:16:17,243
[CHUCKLES]

157
00:16:19,495 --> 00:16:21,814
Careful, rancher, that's Ben
Wade you're talking to.

158
00:16:26,987 --> 00:16:28,153
Well, I need 'em back.

159
00:16:29,639 --> 00:16:30,906
They're all I got.

160
00:16:33,176 --> 00:16:35,594
I don't need your cattle.

161
00:16:35,596 --> 00:16:38,080
But I will be needi''
them horses.

162
00:16:38,082 --> 00:16:42,768
So you don't go doing
nothing...foolish.

163
00:17:04,757 --> 00:17:05,957
Campos.

164
00:17:14,734 --> 00:17:17,102
You'll find them
on the road to Bisbee.

165
00:17:17,104 --> 00:17:18,303
Boys.

166
00:17:23,577 --> 00:17:26,345
[WATCH TICKING]

167
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:35,638
They're probably just running
late, Mr. Butterfield.

168
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:38,090
Pinkertons don't run late.

169
00:17:38,092 --> 00:17:40,325
That's why they're paid
$18 a day.

170
00:17:50,671 --> 00:17:54,173
[DISTANT SHOUTS]

171
00:18:40,353 --> 00:18:41,804
[GRUNTING]

172
00:18:43,340 --> 00:18:44,740
Get me on my feet.

173
00:18:44,742 --> 00:18:46,542
I think you're
in pretty bad shape, mister.

174
00:18:46,544 --> 00:18:49,078
You should--
Just get me on my damn feet.

175
00:18:49,080 --> 00:18:50,913
[GROANING]

176
00:19:01,174 --> 00:19:03,926
Mark, William,
get me some of them boards.

177
00:19:28,001 --> 00:19:29,218
Can I help you?

178
00:19:30,019 --> 00:19:31,771
I think maybe...

179
00:19:31,773 --> 00:19:33,438
a coach headed for here
got itself held up

180
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,357
in the canyon
about 10 miles back...

181
00:19:35,359 --> 00:19:36,792
God damn it.

182
00:19:37,627 --> 00:19:39,778
...by Mr. Ben Wade himself.

183
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:41,864
How did you know
it was Wade?

184
00:19:41,866 --> 00:19:44,433
It's been him the last
21 times, Marshal.

185
00:19:44,435 --> 00:19:46,518
I saw a Mexican sharpshooter
and an Apache.

186
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:48,620
God damn it. Jesus Christ.
And I've been told--

187
00:19:48,622 --> 00:19:50,389
Did you see
The Hand of God?

188
00:19:50,391 --> 00:19:52,190
What's that?
His pistol.

189
00:19:52,192 --> 00:19:53,659
Why the hell didn't
you do something?

190
00:19:55,795 --> 00:19:58,981
They had a lot
of weapons, mister...

191
00:19:58,983 --> 00:20:01,117
and they were
shootin' bullets.

192
00:20:01,119 --> 00:20:02,835
Let's go.
We're wasting time.

193
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:16,982
Where you from, anyway?

194
00:20:21,788 --> 00:20:24,390
Tom Conrad bought
a thousand head in Mexico.

195
00:20:24,392 --> 00:20:26,024
Hired us to drive 'em in.

196
00:20:28,395 --> 00:20:30,412
Let's go.
Come on, boys.

197
00:20:44,928 --> 00:20:47,062
Something's going on
with the railroad man.

198
00:21:39,165 --> 00:21:42,467
Ma'am? Some whiskey
for my friends.

199
00:21:46,706 --> 00:21:47,906
Let's go.
Huh?

200
00:21:47,908 --> 00:21:49,341
The bar's closed.
Already?

201
00:21:53,647 --> 00:21:55,447
[WHISKEY POURING]

202
00:22:04,024 --> 00:22:06,425
[POURING]

203
00:22:14,184 --> 00:22:16,451
Here's to the four
we lost in battle.

204
00:22:18,588 --> 00:22:19,855
And here's
to the boss,

205
00:22:19,857 --> 00:22:21,890
who...

206
00:22:21,892 --> 00:22:24,727
had to say good-bye
to Tommy Darden today.

207
00:22:26,129 --> 00:22:28,097
And that's too bad.

208
00:22:28,099 --> 00:22:29,965
Proverbs 13:3.

209
00:22:32,102 --> 00:22:33,802
"He that keepeth his mouth,

210
00:22:33,804 --> 00:22:35,837
"keepeth his life.

211
00:22:35,839 --> 00:22:37,273
"He that opens
his lips too wide

212
00:22:37,275 --> 00:22:38,707
shall bring on
his own destruction."

213
00:22:38,709 --> 00:22:40,225
Amen.

214
00:22:40,227 --> 00:22:42,160
Tommy was weak.

215
00:22:42,162 --> 00:22:43,979
Tommy was stupid.

216
00:22:43,981 --> 00:22:45,514
Tommy is dead.

217
00:22:48,718 --> 00:22:50,019
I'd drink to that.

218
00:22:56,126 --> 00:22:57,559
Sutherland.

219
00:22:58,795 --> 00:22:59,761
Jorgensen.

220
00:23:04,467 --> 00:23:05,434
Campos.

221
00:23:09,105 --> 00:23:10,372
Jackson.

222
00:23:12,608 --> 00:23:13,776
Kinter.

223
00:23:31,994 --> 00:23:33,529
Marshal's only half stupid.

224
00:23:33,531 --> 00:23:35,230
He's gonna be back soon.

225
00:23:38,802 --> 00:23:40,619
They're going
across the border.

226
00:23:41,838 --> 00:23:43,321
I won't be far.

227
00:23:45,074 --> 00:23:46,257
I'll wait for you.

228
00:23:47,460 --> 00:23:48,644
All right, Charlie.

229
00:24:02,374 --> 00:24:04,109
I've seen you
someplace before.

230
00:24:06,012 --> 00:24:07,278
Have you?

231
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:14,169
You ever work for a blind
Irishman in Leadville?

232
00:24:17,290 --> 00:24:18,423
I was a singer.

233
00:24:21,477 --> 00:24:23,011
The best time
I ever had

234
00:24:23,013 --> 00:24:24,446
in my whole life.

235
00:24:26,349 --> 00:24:27,483
What made you quit?

236
00:24:29,519 --> 00:24:31,320
Got to coughing.

237
00:24:31,322 --> 00:24:34,023
Doctor said I should find
a drier climate.

238
00:24:39,862 --> 00:24:42,631
You know, I spent more money in
that joint than I could tell you.

239
00:24:44,768 --> 00:24:46,468
Do you remember a girl?

240
00:24:47,854 --> 00:24:49,521
Her name was Velvet.

241
00:24:52,575 --> 00:24:54,442
Nobody forgets Velvet.

242
00:25:02,352 --> 00:25:04,119
You look kinda skinny.

243
00:25:09,592 --> 00:25:11,360
I feel skinny.

244
00:25:12,762 --> 00:25:14,379
That's all right.

245
00:25:16,749 --> 00:25:18,417
I don't mind skinny girls.

246
00:25:20,469 --> 00:25:22,887
Long as they got green eyes
to make up for it.

247
00:25:25,825 --> 00:25:27,225
Have you got green eyes?

248
00:25:39,756 --> 00:25:41,923
That's all right.

249
00:25:41,925 --> 00:25:43,325
They don't have
to be green.

250
00:25:54,137 --> 00:25:56,238
Do you think they lied?

251
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:58,740
Do you think they stole
our horses?

252
00:25:58,742 --> 00:26:00,242
They don't need
our shit horses.

253
00:26:00,244 --> 00:26:01,710
Watch your mouth.

254
00:26:14,457 --> 00:26:16,758
I'll take him into town
on my own.

255
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:20,245
You boys go round up
the herd.

256
00:26:20,247 --> 00:26:22,648
Don't push them too hard.
I can't afford any more dropping.

257
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:24,750
Mister, we're gonna have
to lift you up

258
00:26:24,752 --> 00:26:26,385
to get you on top
of that horse.

259
00:26:27,453 --> 00:26:29,104
Here comes the Cavalry.

260
00:26:33,793 --> 00:26:35,227
Do as I said.

261
00:26:41,968 --> 00:26:44,269
Is he from the coach?

262
00:26:44,271 --> 00:26:45,687
Only one who made it.

263
00:26:45,689 --> 00:26:47,940
Mr. McElroy,
can you hear me?

264
00:26:47,942 --> 00:26:49,207
It was Ben Wade.

265
00:26:49,209 --> 00:26:51,193
Mr. McElroy,
can you hear me?

266
00:26:51,195 --> 00:26:52,611
Mr. Mc--

267
00:26:52,613 --> 00:26:54,946
This man needs attention.

268
00:26:54,948 --> 00:26:56,982
You see which way
he rode, Evans?

269
00:26:56,984 --> 00:26:59,118
Looked like they
were headed to Bisbee.

270
00:27:15,935 --> 00:27:18,170
MAN [IN DISTANCE]:
Hey! Yah!

271
00:27:18,172 --> 00:27:19,304
Hey!

272
00:27:50,236 --> 00:27:52,404
You know...

273
00:27:52,406 --> 00:27:55,006
there's a little town
just south of the border...

274
00:27:56,742 --> 00:27:59,594
<i>pretty little pueblucho
down by the river.</i>

275
00:28:01,848 --> 00:28:04,549
Folks would pay good money
to hear a white woman sing.

276
00:28:06,251 --> 00:28:08,620
[CHUCKLES]
Yeah.

277
00:28:08,622 --> 00:28:10,689
Imagine me shinning
on down to Mexico

278
00:28:10,691 --> 00:28:12,491
with Ben Wade on my arm.

279
00:28:14,861 --> 00:28:16,561
I'm not wanted
in Mexico.

280
00:28:19,598 --> 00:28:21,916
Jump out that back window
with me now.

281
00:28:26,906 --> 00:28:28,707
You're crazy.

282
00:28:33,146 --> 00:28:34,213
You the doctor?

283
00:28:34,215 --> 00:28:35,547
Yes.

284
00:28:35,549 --> 00:28:37,399
Coach got held up.
Get him on the table.

285
00:28:45,508 --> 00:28:47,276
[SIGHS]

286
00:28:47,278 --> 00:28:49,478
What's his name?
Byron McElroy.

287
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,780
He's a bounty hunter under
contract with the Pinkertons.

288
00:29:00,556 --> 00:29:02,290
DOCTOR: You've lost a lot
of blood, Mr. McElroy.

289
00:29:08,631 --> 00:29:10,298
That bullet's still
in there.

290
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:12,234
Well, get it out.

291
00:29:22,128 --> 00:29:24,195
All right.
[MOANS]

292
00:29:24,197 --> 00:29:26,998
Now, what I'm about to do is gonna
hurt like a son of a bitch.

293
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,734
Ain't the first time
I been shot.

294
00:29:29,736 --> 00:29:31,786
Hold him, please.

295
00:29:35,308 --> 00:29:36,641
Don't touch me.

296
00:29:40,879 --> 00:29:42,414
DOCTOR:
All right.

297
00:29:48,955 --> 00:29:50,805
[EXHALES]
[SQUELCHING]

298
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:53,174
[GROANING]

299
00:30:03,586 --> 00:30:04,686
[EXHALES]

300
00:30:15,514 --> 00:30:19,534
What the fuck kind of
doctor are you, anyway?

301
00:30:19,536 --> 00:30:22,270
It's nice to have a conversation
with a patient for a change.

302
00:30:22,272 --> 00:30:23,705
[CHUCKLES]

303
00:30:23,707 --> 00:30:25,506
MAN: You see
anything down there?

304
00:30:28,978 --> 00:30:29,894
[MAN WHISTLES]

305
00:30:29,896 --> 00:30:31,830
Marshal.
Wade's horse.

306
00:30:33,433 --> 00:30:35,834
Take the back.
We'll take the front.

307
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,667
What the hell
are they looking for?

308
00:30:54,988 --> 00:30:56,821
Ben Wade.

309
00:30:56,823 --> 00:30:58,523
He held up
the payroll coach.

310
00:31:00,759 --> 00:31:02,260
I want to talk,
Mr. Hollander.

311
00:31:02,262 --> 00:31:03,961
Ben Wade in Bisbee.

312
00:31:03,963 --> 00:31:05,163
Shit.

313
00:31:05,165 --> 00:31:06,998
We're movin' up.

314
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,466
Mr. Hollander?

315
00:31:08,468 --> 00:31:10,235
Tucker, go on
to the saloon.

316
00:31:10,237 --> 00:31:12,404
You got no right
to do what you done.

317
00:31:12,406 --> 00:31:14,088
You hear me?

318
00:31:14,090 --> 00:31:15,256
That's my land.

319
00:31:15,258 --> 00:31:16,424
Come next week
it's not, Evans.

320
00:31:16,426 --> 00:31:17,759
You borrowed
a good deal of money

321
00:31:17,761 --> 00:31:19,360
and I got rights
to recompense.

322
00:31:19,362 --> 00:31:22,363
But you dammed up my creek.
You shut off my water.

323
00:31:22,365 --> 00:31:24,231
How'd you expect me to pay
off my debts if you can't--

324
00:31:26,001 --> 00:31:27,352
Before the water
touches your land,

325
00:31:27,354 --> 00:31:29,671
it resides and flows
on mine.

326
00:31:29,673 --> 00:31:32,623
And as such, I can do with
it as I fuckin' please.

327
00:31:32,625 --> 00:31:34,075
Go home and pack up.

328
00:31:35,878 --> 00:31:37,112
Can you--

329
00:31:37,114 --> 00:31:38,813
Can you just
let me get to spring?

330
00:31:43,802 --> 00:31:45,570
I can turn the corner.

331
00:31:47,874 --> 00:31:50,992
Sometimes a man has to be big
enough to see how small he is.

332
00:31:53,763 --> 00:31:56,531
Railroad's coming, Dan.

333
00:31:56,533 --> 00:31:58,516
Your land's worth more
with you off it.

334
00:32:04,073 --> 00:32:05,557
[CHUCKLES]

335
00:32:26,245 --> 00:32:27,712
[COCKS RIFLE]

336
00:32:36,188 --> 00:32:37,322
Hollander!

337
00:32:48,601 --> 00:32:49,901
[SIGHS]

338
00:32:49,903 --> 00:32:51,436
You look a little
bent, rancher.

339
00:32:52,871 --> 00:32:55,507
You come to wake
some snakes?

340
00:32:55,509 --> 00:32:57,725
WOMAN:
Dan, would you like a drink?

341
00:32:57,727 --> 00:32:59,277
No, thanks.

342
00:32:59,279 --> 00:33:00,929
You got your horses back,
didn't you?

343
00:33:00,931 --> 00:33:01,863
And your cattle?

344
00:33:04,567 --> 00:33:07,035
Yeah, I got
my horses back.

345
00:33:07,037 --> 00:33:09,403
But you killed
two of my herd.

346
00:33:09,405 --> 00:33:11,573
Well, they died
for a good cause.

347
00:33:14,793 --> 00:33:16,761
You know...

348
00:33:16,763 --> 00:33:19,464
them beeves of yours,

349
00:33:19,466 --> 00:33:21,349
they wouldn't even
have fed a hungry dog.

350
00:33:23,886 --> 00:33:25,587
I tell you what.
[COINS SLIDING]

351
00:33:26,655 --> 00:33:28,372
That should cover it.

352
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:34,061
How much you get
for a day's work?

353
00:33:34,063 --> 00:33:35,930
$2 when I hire out.

354
00:33:35,932 --> 00:33:37,765
Well, there are $2
for a half a day.

355
00:33:37,767 --> 00:33:39,333
[COINS CLATTER]

356
00:33:43,822 --> 00:33:46,240
You took up
my boys' time, too.

357
00:33:50,829 --> 00:33:53,014
You're right, I did.
[COINS CLINKING]

358
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:55,750
[COINS SLIDING]

359
00:34:02,158 --> 00:34:05,109
Anything else you wanna
get paid for, Dan?

360
00:34:08,396 --> 00:34:10,448
You can give me
$5 extra.

361
00:34:12,535 --> 00:34:14,368
And what's that for?

362
00:34:14,370 --> 00:34:16,487
For making me nervous.

363
00:34:16,489 --> 00:34:18,122
[WOOD CREAKING]

364
00:34:18,124 --> 00:34:20,792
Hands up, Ben Wade.

365
00:34:20,794 --> 00:34:22,777
Boss! Boss!

366
00:34:22,779 --> 00:34:24,145
Hey, Boss!

367
00:34:27,633 --> 00:34:29,434
Gimme your hands,
Mr. Wade.

368
00:34:29,436 --> 00:34:31,836
Tucker, take his gun.
TUCKER: Gimme that.

369
00:34:33,822 --> 00:34:35,223
Ben Wade...

370
00:34:38,894 --> 00:34:40,228
captured in Bisbee.

371
00:34:41,864 --> 00:34:43,547
Be careful
with that thing.

372
00:34:43,549 --> 00:34:45,099
That gun's got
a curse on it.

373
00:34:46,285 --> 00:34:47,985
[CHUCKLES]

374
00:34:47,987 --> 00:34:51,789
Laugh while you can.
Crawley, go get the wagon.

375
00:34:51,791 --> 00:34:54,793
Make sure every weapon we got
is shoot-ready.

376
00:34:54,795 --> 00:34:56,660
I'll meet you out front
of the office.

377
00:34:56,662 --> 00:34:58,296
We gotta get him
outta here.

378
00:34:58,298 --> 00:34:59,864
Sure thing.

379
00:34:59,866 --> 00:35:02,166
I think we should
shoot him right now.

380
00:35:02,168 --> 00:35:03,634
Hmm?

381
00:35:03,636 --> 00:35:04,835
Put a bullet right

382
00:35:04,837 --> 00:35:05,920
in his noggin.

383
00:35:05,922 --> 00:35:07,588
Do that...everybody

384
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:08,890
in this shit-piss
little town

385
00:35:08,892 --> 00:35:10,775
will be dead by morning.

386
00:35:17,099 --> 00:35:21,035
22 robberies.

387
00:35:21,037 --> 00:35:23,871
Over $400,000
in losses.

388
00:35:23,873 --> 00:35:26,424
More in delays.

389
00:35:26,426 --> 00:35:28,376
The Southern Pacific

390
00:35:28,378 --> 00:35:32,213
will have Ben Wade convicted
in a federal court.

391
00:35:32,215 --> 00:35:36,167
Hanged in public.

392
00:35:36,169 --> 00:35:38,352
An example made.

393
00:35:38,354 --> 00:35:41,006
And we will pay
to make it happen.

394
00:35:41,008 --> 00:35:43,791
Y'all notice he didn't mention
any of the lives I've taken.

395
00:35:43,793 --> 00:35:45,543
MARSHAL:
I need three more men.

396
00:35:45,545 --> 00:35:48,012
You can have Tucker.
Good.

397
00:35:48,014 --> 00:35:50,282
I'm coming.
You only need one.

398
00:35:50,284 --> 00:35:52,767
MARSHAL: You're
wounded, Mr. McElroy.

399
00:35:52,769 --> 00:35:56,170
I rode in here.
Sure as hell can ride out.

400
00:35:56,172 --> 00:35:57,655
He goes,
Potter's coming.

401
00:35:57,657 --> 00:35:59,107
What?

402
00:35:59,109 --> 00:36:00,608
[SCOFFS]

403
00:36:00,610 --> 00:36:02,543
Doc can't shoot shit.

404
00:36:02,545 --> 00:36:05,079
DAN: I was best
shot in my regiment.

405
00:36:05,081 --> 00:36:06,464
I'll come...

406
00:36:09,118 --> 00:36:11,302
for $200.

407
00:36:13,555 --> 00:36:15,189
You fight for the North
or the South?

408
00:36:16,809 --> 00:36:18,760
North.

409
00:36:18,762 --> 00:36:20,694
We're Southern
in name,

410
00:36:20,696 --> 00:36:22,313
but Chicago owned.

411
00:36:22,315 --> 00:36:24,199
Fine. $200.

412
00:36:25,267 --> 00:36:26,601
MARSHAL:
Let's go.

413
00:36:37,996 --> 00:36:40,832
Thank you.
Thank me when it's done.

414
00:36:49,008 --> 00:36:50,375
MAN: 
What's goin' on?

415
00:37:10,946 --> 00:37:13,248
DRIVER:
Whoa! Whoa!

416
00:37:17,302 --> 00:37:18,969
This town's gonna burn!

417
00:37:21,890 --> 00:37:24,025
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

418
00:37:24,027 --> 00:37:26,060
Let's get him, Mark!
Cover me!

419
00:37:26,062 --> 00:37:27,394
[MEN SHOUTING]

420
00:37:29,614 --> 00:37:30,781
MAN: 
Shoot!

421
00:37:33,285 --> 00:37:34,469
MAN: 
Get him!

422
00:37:36,605 --> 00:37:38,172
Get in the coach.

423
00:37:50,135 --> 00:37:52,236
God damn it.

424
00:37:52,238 --> 00:37:56,273
Evans, Crawley, Tucker,
you need to mount up now.

425
00:37:56,275 --> 00:37:57,859
Head for Evans Ranch.

426
00:37:57,861 --> 00:37:59,427
I'll meet you there
with the coach.

427
00:38:15,894 --> 00:38:18,195
How long does he have
to be here?

428
00:38:18,197 --> 00:38:20,064
An hour...

429
00:38:20,066 --> 00:38:22,516
to make sure his outfit
takes the bait.

430
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,174
[LOUD CLATTER]
[HORSE NEIGHS]

431
00:38:33,729 --> 00:38:35,180
[CATTLE MOOING]

432
00:38:41,353 --> 00:38:43,220
[HORSE WHINNIES]

433
00:38:51,947 --> 00:38:53,514
Hello, there!

434
00:38:53,516 --> 00:38:56,183
Evans! Can you give me
a hand with this?

435
00:39:05,427 --> 00:39:08,129
Whatever your wife's
cooking in there,

436
00:39:08,131 --> 00:39:09,597
it smells good,
Evans.

437
00:39:25,881 --> 00:39:27,214
[COCKS GUN]

438
00:39:27,216 --> 00:39:28,366
Let's go.

439
00:39:31,570 --> 00:39:32,937
Good driving, Marshal.

440
00:39:47,586 --> 00:39:50,187
Remind me not to play poker
in this town.

441
00:39:51,190 --> 00:39:53,124
All right, Marshal.

442
00:39:53,126 --> 00:39:54,692
Give us a count.

443
00:39:54,694 --> 00:39:58,146
One, two, three.
Yah!

444
00:40:01,633 --> 00:40:03,067
Whoa.

445
00:40:16,615 --> 00:40:18,483
Good luck.

446
00:40:18,485 --> 00:40:19,683
You're gonna check
on my family

447
00:40:19,685 --> 00:40:21,619
when you come back, right?
First thing.

448
00:40:21,621 --> 00:40:23,104
Let's go.
Hyah!

449
00:40:28,243 --> 00:40:29,677
Hyah!

450
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,179
Ma'am.

451
00:40:50,515 --> 00:40:52,016
Byron...

452
00:40:52,018 --> 00:40:53,751
what an unpleasant surprise.

453
00:40:56,321 --> 00:40:59,156
What happens if they
catch the wagon?

454
00:40:59,158 --> 00:41:00,324
Well...

455
00:41:00,326 --> 00:41:02,009
you saw where his man was.

456
00:41:02,011 --> 00:41:03,578
He still gotta go
fetch the outfit.

457
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:05,012
Marshal's got a fast rig.

458
00:41:05,014 --> 00:41:07,181
They should reach
the fort before dawn.

459
00:41:07,183 --> 00:41:10,334
His gang can't do anything in
front of the whole 6th Cavalry.

460
00:41:25,517 --> 00:41:27,268
Did you have something
to do with that?

461
00:41:30,422 --> 00:41:32,489
I hope you're proud
of yourself.

462
00:41:35,627 --> 00:41:38,029
Just doin' my job, Doc.

463
00:41:41,033 --> 00:41:42,834
Thanks, son.

464
00:42:02,170 --> 00:42:04,105
We always wait to say grace.

465
00:42:04,107 --> 00:42:07,275
We don't presume to teach
other people manners.

466
00:42:07,277 --> 00:42:09,444
Aren't we supposed to say
grace for murderers, too?

467
00:42:09,446 --> 00:42:11,813
Grace is
for everyone, dear.

468
00:42:11,815 --> 00:42:13,931
Then why don't we say it?
Mark.

469
00:42:13,933 --> 00:42:15,733
MCELROY:
I'd like to hear it.

470
00:42:22,340 --> 00:42:23,775
God our Father,
Lord, and Savior,

471
00:42:23,777 --> 00:42:25,560
thank You for Your
love and favor.

472
00:42:25,562 --> 00:42:28,479
Please bless this drink
and food, we pray.

473
00:42:28,481 --> 00:42:31,649
Bless all who shares
with us today.

474
00:42:31,651 --> 00:42:32,633
Amen.

475
00:42:32,635 --> 00:42:34,184
Amen.

476
00:42:34,186 --> 00:42:35,703
Amen.

477
00:42:35,705 --> 00:42:39,307
If my pa wants to,
he could shoot you dead.

478
00:42:39,309 --> 00:42:41,943
He can shoot a jackrabbit
at 50 yards.

479
00:42:41,945 --> 00:42:43,344
[CHUCKLES]

480
00:42:43,346 --> 00:42:44,845
Shooting an animal's
a lot different

481
00:42:44,847 --> 00:42:47,148
than, uh,
shooting a man, son.

482
00:42:47,150 --> 00:42:48,866
WADE:
No, it isn't.

483
00:42:50,535 --> 00:42:52,770
Not in my opinion.

484
00:42:54,422 --> 00:42:55,706
We could ask Byron here.

485
00:42:55,708 --> 00:42:59,359
Now, Byron, he's killed
dozens of people:

486
00:42:59,361 --> 00:43:02,346
men and women
and children,

487
00:43:02,348 --> 00:43:03,548
miners, Apache.

488
00:43:03,550 --> 00:43:04,782
Not a soul taken

489
00:43:04,784 --> 00:43:06,767
didn't deserve what it got.

490
00:43:08,504 --> 00:43:13,740
Every way of man is right
in his own eyes, Byron.

491
00:43:13,742 --> 00:43:15,176
The Lord ponders the heart.

492
00:43:18,180 --> 00:43:19,513
Proverbs 21.

493
00:43:35,297 --> 00:43:36,263
Dan.

494
00:43:42,704 --> 00:43:45,373
WADE: You eat more when you're
nervous, Mr. Butterfield?

495
00:43:46,475 --> 00:43:47,891
Oh, why, thank you, Dan.

496
00:43:47,893 --> 00:43:50,427
That would be pleasant
and kind of you.

497
00:43:50,429 --> 00:43:51,512
Much appreciated.

498
00:43:51,514 --> 00:43:53,714
You can cut
that up for me.

499
00:43:55,083 --> 00:43:56,583
Oh, can you cut
the fat off there?

500
00:43:56,585 --> 00:43:58,368
I don't particularly
like the fat at all.

501
00:43:58,370 --> 00:44:00,203
[MUTTERING]
I-I just--

502
00:44:01,857 --> 00:44:03,374
And the--

503
00:44:04,509 --> 00:44:05,676
And the gristle.

504
00:44:05,678 --> 00:44:07,678
I don't like
the gristle.

505
00:44:12,634 --> 00:44:15,969
You mind if I ask you how you got
that hitch in your step, Dan?

506
00:44:15,971 --> 00:44:18,339
BYRON: Don't tell him nothing,
Mr. Evans.

507
00:44:22,260 --> 00:44:24,178
Where were you stationed?

508
00:44:26,047 --> 00:44:27,748
Second Company
Sharpshooters

509
00:44:27,750 --> 00:44:30,017
out of Lynnfield,
Massachusetts.

510
00:44:34,740 --> 00:44:37,425
My father was defending
the U.S. capitol

511
00:44:37,427 --> 00:44:39,009
in the District
of Columbia.

512
00:44:39,011 --> 00:44:40,061
Is that so?

513
00:44:40,063 --> 00:44:42,045
Well, Dan,

514
00:44:42,047 --> 00:44:44,448
tell me the story
of how you lost your leg.

515
00:44:44,450 --> 00:44:47,301
Did it get shot off,
cut off?

516
00:44:47,303 --> 00:44:49,570
The Indians steal it?

517
00:44:50,823 --> 00:44:53,357
[GUNSHOTS]

518
00:44:55,727 --> 00:44:58,595
[GUNSHOTS]

519
00:45:00,481 --> 00:45:02,933
There's something moving
out there in the grass.

520
00:45:11,843 --> 00:45:13,828
There ain't nothing.

521
00:45:18,349 --> 00:45:20,784
MAN [IN DISTANCE]:
I think I saw something over the ridge.

522
00:45:22,186 --> 00:45:23,703
What if they caught
the coach already?

523
00:45:23,705 --> 00:45:25,972
What if they already know
it's Crawley inside?

524
00:45:30,144 --> 00:45:32,913
You ever been
to San Francisco?

525
00:45:34,783 --> 00:45:37,018
If it's all right
by you, Mr. Wade,

526
00:45:37,020 --> 00:45:39,487
I'd rather we not talk.

527
00:45:39,489 --> 00:45:43,140
So you've never been
to San Francisco.

528
00:45:43,142 --> 00:45:44,608
No.

529
00:45:48,313 --> 00:45:50,214
I knew a girl there.

530
00:45:50,216 --> 00:45:52,983
She was the daughter
of a sea captain.

531
00:45:52,985 --> 00:45:57,071
She had the most
beautiful green eyes,

532
00:45:57,073 --> 00:45:59,940
about the greenest eyes
I ever saw.

533
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:08,415
Like yours.

534
00:46:11,252 --> 00:46:13,354
And I'd stare deep
into them.

535
00:46:13,356 --> 00:46:15,589
They'd just change
color in front of me.

536
00:46:15,591 --> 00:46:17,691
All the colors
of the sea.

537
00:46:26,968 --> 00:46:29,052
What did you say
your name was again?

538
00:46:29,054 --> 00:46:30,921
Alice?

539
00:46:35,994 --> 00:46:37,094
Alice.

540
00:46:44,503 --> 00:46:46,303
For God's sake.

541
00:46:46,305 --> 00:46:48,272
He's killed more men
than the drought.

542
00:46:48,274 --> 00:46:50,391
He's not what I expected.
He's--

543
00:46:50,393 --> 00:46:51,842
He's dangerous.

544
00:46:51,844 --> 00:46:54,044
Dangerous is what
he is, Alice.

545
00:46:54,046 --> 00:46:56,380
I don't want you or the
boys talking to him.

546
00:46:58,933 --> 00:47:01,502
You can change
your mind, Dan.

547
00:47:01,504 --> 00:47:04,054
No one will
think less of you.

548
00:47:05,607 --> 00:47:07,874
No one can think less of me.

549
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:11,812
Six months from now,

550
00:47:11,814 --> 00:47:14,398
everything's
going to be green.

551
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:16,634
The cows are
going to be fat.

552
00:47:16,636 --> 00:47:18,185
We might even see
the steam

553
00:47:18,187 --> 00:47:21,739
from the train
coming over the ridge.

554
00:47:21,741 --> 00:47:24,791
We'll be all right.

555
00:47:24,793 --> 00:47:28,479
But we won't make it
through the next six days

556
00:47:28,481 --> 00:47:30,697
if I don't do this.

557
00:47:31,783 --> 00:47:33,217
[KNOCKING]

558
00:47:34,953 --> 00:47:36,453
Sorry, Dan.

559
00:47:36,455 --> 00:47:38,105
McElroy says
five minutes.

560
00:47:50,368 --> 00:47:54,220
You think
he's too much for me?

561
00:47:54,222 --> 00:47:57,140
He's a killer, Daniel.

562
00:47:57,142 --> 00:48:00,461
Then someone ought
to have the decency

563
00:48:00,463 --> 00:48:02,013
to bring him to justice.

564
00:48:05,133 --> 00:48:07,167
[SCOFFS]

565
00:48:07,169 --> 00:48:09,269
What are you thinking?

566
00:48:10,739 --> 00:48:12,923
I'm not out there alone,
you know.

567
00:48:12,925 --> 00:48:15,542
Have a little faith in me.

568
00:48:15,544 --> 00:48:17,478
Ben Wade has a gang,

569
00:48:17,480 --> 00:48:20,013
and they're out there
tonight somewhere.

570
00:48:20,015 --> 00:48:23,600
If I don't go, we got
to pack up and leave,

571
00:48:23,602 --> 00:48:24,968
and God knows where,

572
00:48:24,970 --> 00:48:26,336
without a prayer,
dirt-poor.

573
00:48:26,338 --> 00:48:27,971
Now I'm tired, Alice.

574
00:48:27,973 --> 00:48:30,991
I am tired of watching
my boys go hungry.

575
00:48:30,993 --> 00:48:33,143
I'm tired of the way
that they look at me.

576
00:48:33,145 --> 00:48:36,363
I'm tired of the way
that you don't.

577
00:48:36,365 --> 00:48:40,017
I've been standing
on one leg

578
00:48:40,019 --> 00:48:42,035
for three damn years,

579
00:48:42,037 --> 00:48:43,970
waiting for God
to do me a favor.

580
00:48:46,841 --> 00:48:49,009
And He ain't listening.

581
00:48:49,011 --> 00:48:50,361
[KNOCKING]

582
00:48:50,363 --> 00:48:52,112
BUTTERFIELD:
Mr. Evans.

583
00:49:02,841 --> 00:49:05,325
Oh, no, no, no, no.

584
00:49:06,427 --> 00:49:08,028
This is my horse now.

585
00:49:11,516 --> 00:49:13,016
Come on over here.

586
00:49:14,552 --> 00:49:15,819
Come on.

587
00:49:21,025 --> 00:49:23,093
Don't you
be any trouble, Mark.

588
00:49:23,095 --> 00:49:24,828
Yes, sir.
All right.

589
00:49:28,049 --> 00:49:29,750
William.

590
00:49:29,752 --> 00:49:31,384
I want to come
with you.

591
00:49:31,386 --> 00:49:32,619
Well, you can't.

592
00:49:32,621 --> 00:49:33,903
I could help.

593
00:49:33,905 --> 00:49:35,288
You're 14 years old.

594
00:49:35,290 --> 00:49:37,525
Look, I can ride faster
and shoot better

595
00:49:37,527 --> 00:49:39,126
than any one of them.

596
00:49:39,128 --> 00:49:41,611
The Pinkerton's hurt,
Potter's no good,

597
00:49:41,613 --> 00:49:43,513
that railroad man's
dead weight,

598
00:49:43,515 --> 00:49:44,748
and that other bastard--
William.

599
00:49:44,750 --> 00:49:45,882
William.

600
00:49:45,884 --> 00:49:47,051
I don't have time
to argue.

601
00:49:47,053 --> 00:49:50,136
I need you here.
That's that.

602
00:49:50,138 --> 00:49:51,705
That's that.

603
00:49:57,078 --> 00:49:59,896
So, boys,
where are we headed?

604
00:49:59,898 --> 00:50:02,049
Ain't none of your business
where we're headed, Wade.

605
00:50:02,051 --> 00:50:03,783
You're a prisoner.

606
00:50:03,785 --> 00:50:06,954
You don't speak,
you don't piss,

607
00:50:06,956 --> 00:50:10,223
you don't goddamn breathe
unless we say so.

608
00:50:10,225 --> 00:50:11,909
You understand that?

609
00:50:15,329 --> 00:50:17,664
We're taking you
to Contention.

610
00:50:17,666 --> 00:50:21,101
Putting you on the 3:10 to Yuma
day after tomorrow.

611
00:50:21,103 --> 00:50:22,869
You shouldn't have
told him that.

612
00:50:24,472 --> 00:50:26,172
Relax, friend.

613
00:50:26,174 --> 00:50:28,875
Now if we get separated,
I know where to meet up.

614
00:50:32,514 --> 00:50:35,315
I'd like to thank you
for your hospitality, ma'am.

615
00:50:35,317 --> 00:50:38,017
Hope I can send your
husband back all right.

616
00:50:42,323 --> 00:50:43,773
[CLICKS TONGUE]

617
00:51:02,243 --> 00:51:03,927
[COUGHING]

618
00:51:12,286 --> 00:51:13,971
What did Ben Wade mean

619
00:51:13,973 --> 00:51:15,389
about sending Pa
back all right?

620
00:51:15,391 --> 00:51:17,541
Was he saying
he was gonna kill him?

621
00:51:17,543 --> 00:51:19,709
WILLIAM: Ben Wade don't
have to lift a finger.

622
00:51:19,711 --> 00:51:21,962
His gang will do it for him.

623
00:51:24,382 --> 00:51:27,084
Your father can
take care of himself.

624
00:51:42,150 --> 00:51:43,217
Shh.

625
00:52:12,780 --> 00:52:14,414
So...

626
00:52:14,416 --> 00:52:17,701
were you conscripted into
Lincoln's army, Mr. Evans,

627
00:52:17,703 --> 00:52:19,269
or did you volunteer?

628
00:52:19,271 --> 00:52:20,537
Neither.

629
00:52:23,157 --> 00:52:24,324
Maybe both.

630
00:52:24,326 --> 00:52:26,910
What does that mean?

631
00:52:26,912 --> 00:52:29,012
Means I was a volunteer

632
00:52:29,014 --> 00:52:31,081
in the Massachusetts
State Guard.

633
00:52:31,083 --> 00:52:33,951
Then, in '62,

634
00:52:33,953 --> 00:52:35,536
the federal government
was running low on men,

635
00:52:35,538 --> 00:52:37,620
so they called in
the state militias

636
00:52:37,622 --> 00:52:39,906
to protect Washington.

637
00:52:39,908 --> 00:52:42,009
And that's
when you got hurt.

638
00:52:45,997 --> 00:52:48,899
What are you doing
out here, Dan?

639
00:52:48,901 --> 00:52:52,252
You got a family
to protect.

640
00:52:52,254 --> 00:52:53,803
You're not a lawman.

641
00:52:53,805 --> 00:52:55,138
You don't work
for the railroad

642
00:52:55,140 --> 00:52:57,290
like Mr. Shiny Shoes
over there.

643
00:52:57,292 --> 00:52:59,076
You're not a Pinkerton.

644
00:52:59,078 --> 00:53:01,578
Maybe I don't like the idea

645
00:53:01,580 --> 00:53:03,930
of men like you
on the loose.

646
00:53:03,932 --> 00:53:07,751
It's man's nature
to take what he wants, Dan.

647
00:53:07,753 --> 00:53:09,719
That's how we're born.

648
00:53:11,556 --> 00:53:14,274
Well, I make an honest living.

649
00:53:14,276 --> 00:53:15,775
It might be honest,

650
00:53:15,777 --> 00:53:17,927
but I don't think
it's much of a living.

651
00:53:17,929 --> 00:53:20,380
You must be hurting bad
for money to take this job.

652
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:24,501
Go to sleep.

653
00:53:28,422 --> 00:53:30,490
I imagine debt puts

654
00:53:30,492 --> 00:53:31,741
a lot of pressure
on a marriage.

655
00:53:31,743 --> 00:53:34,277
You imagine?

656
00:53:34,279 --> 00:53:36,613
What would you know
about marriage?

657
00:53:36,615 --> 00:53:40,250
We can't all be
cutthroats and thieves.

658
00:53:40,252 --> 00:53:42,919
I know if I was lucky enough
to have a wife like Alice,

659
00:53:42,921 --> 00:53:45,973
I'd treat her a whole lot
better than you do, Dan.

660
00:53:45,975 --> 00:53:49,259
I'd feed her better,
buy her pretty dresses,

661
00:53:49,261 --> 00:53:51,995
wouldn't make her
work so hard.

662
00:53:53,798 --> 00:53:55,482
Yeah, I'll bet Alice

663
00:53:55,484 --> 00:53:57,133
was a real pretty girl
before she married you.

664
00:53:57,135 --> 00:53:59,336
Shut up about my wife.

665
00:53:59,338 --> 00:54:01,104
You shut up about her.

666
00:54:01,106 --> 00:54:02,355
You say one more word,

667
00:54:02,357 --> 00:54:05,391
and I'll cut you down
right here.

668
00:54:05,393 --> 00:54:06,577
Right here.

669
00:54:07,962 --> 00:54:10,380
I like this side
of you, Dan.

670
00:54:10,382 --> 00:54:12,383
Mr. Evans.

671
00:54:16,020 --> 00:54:17,220
Okay.

672
00:54:19,390 --> 00:54:21,458
It's my watch now.

673
00:54:44,682 --> 00:54:48,285
♪ [MAN SINGING IN DISTANCE]

674
00:54:54,525 --> 00:54:57,343
♪ They're gonna hang me in the mornin' ♪

675
00:54:58,445 --> 00:55:00,831
♪ Before the night is done ♪

676
00:55:02,533 --> 00:55:05,268
♪ They're gonna hang me in the mornin' ♪

677
00:55:05,270 --> 00:55:08,338
♪ I'll never see the sun ♪

678
00:55:08,340 --> 00:55:11,942
I suppose it's too much
to ask for a little quiet.

679
00:55:11,944 --> 00:55:13,177
Huh.

680
00:55:13,179 --> 00:55:15,228
The way I figured it

681
00:55:15,230 --> 00:55:17,614
is I'd be asleep
in my own bed right now

682
00:55:17,616 --> 00:55:19,833
if it weren't for you.

683
00:55:19,835 --> 00:55:21,551
So if I got to be up,

684
00:55:21,553 --> 00:55:24,938
well, then, you're damn well
gonna be up with me, too,

685
00:55:24,940 --> 00:55:27,791
Ben Wade.

686
00:55:31,979 --> 00:55:35,315
♪ They're gonna hang me in the mornin' ♪

687
00:55:35,317 --> 00:55:38,085
♪ Before the night is done ♪

688
00:55:40,120 --> 00:55:42,288
♪ Hang me in the mornin' ♪

689
00:55:42,290 --> 00:55:46,460
[COCKS]
♪ I'll never see the sun ♪

690
00:55:54,151 --> 00:55:55,852
[CHOKING]
[POUNDING]

691
00:56:00,090 --> 00:56:02,359
Son of a bitch!

692
00:56:17,959 --> 00:56:19,359
Enough.

693
00:56:21,929 --> 00:56:23,396
Heh heh heh.

694
00:56:23,398 --> 00:56:24,681
Enough!

695
00:56:24,683 --> 00:56:26,349
That's enough, McElroy.

696
00:56:34,942 --> 00:56:38,862
[CHUCKLING]

697
00:56:38,864 --> 00:56:40,697
We have to bury him.

698
00:56:42,049 --> 00:56:45,669
Take the time
to dig one grave,

699
00:56:45,671 --> 00:56:48,288
might as well dig one
for yourself.

700
00:56:51,375 --> 00:56:52,792
Let's go.

701
00:56:52,794 --> 00:56:54,211
Mount up.

702
00:56:54,213 --> 00:56:59,098
♪ Gonna hang me in the mornin' ♪

703
00:56:59,100 --> 00:57:00,583
[CHUCKLING]

704
00:57:04,822 --> 00:57:07,207
♪ I'll never see the sun ♪

705
00:57:07,209 --> 00:57:08,175
[CHUCKLING]

706
00:57:45,746 --> 00:57:47,213
Yah!

707
00:57:52,770 --> 00:57:54,937
Yah! Yah!

708
00:57:56,407 --> 00:57:57,540
Yah!

709
00:57:57,542 --> 00:57:58,708
[GUNSHOT]

710
00:58:22,417 --> 00:58:23,883
Don't you worry there, Boss.

711
00:58:23,885 --> 00:58:25,718
We're gonna get you
outta there in a second.

712
00:58:30,491 --> 00:58:32,125
Charlie!

713
00:58:40,584 --> 00:58:41,517
Wait! Wait!

714
00:58:45,189 --> 00:58:46,439
Sutherland.

715
00:58:50,611 --> 00:58:51,778
Jackson.

716
00:58:55,482 --> 00:58:56,666
No.

717
00:58:59,904 --> 00:59:01,671
[FIRE ERUPTS]
No.

718
00:59:01,673 --> 00:59:02,722
Don't do this.

719
00:59:04,091 --> 00:59:06,326
Don't do this.

720
00:59:06,328 --> 00:59:07,260
Don't do this.

721
00:59:08,979 --> 00:59:11,097
Where is he?
Open the door.

722
00:59:11,099 --> 00:59:13,016
Open the door.
Let me outta here, Goddamn it.

723
00:59:13,018 --> 00:59:15,752
Where did they take him?
I don't know.

724
00:59:19,423 --> 00:59:21,942
Mister...

725
00:59:21,944 --> 00:59:23,176
you better tell me...

726
00:59:23,178 --> 00:59:25,678
where they took him...

727
00:59:25,680 --> 00:59:27,180
or you will burn.

728
00:59:27,182 --> 00:59:29,399
[COUGHING]

729
00:59:32,002 --> 00:59:34,671
Contention.
All right?

730
00:59:34,673 --> 00:59:37,507
They're going to Contention.

731
00:59:37,509 --> 00:59:40,577
They're gonna put him on the
3:10 to Yuma Prison tomorrow.

732
00:59:45,282 --> 00:59:46,833
Let me outta here!

733
00:59:47,734 --> 00:59:49,853
[SCREAMING]

734
00:59:49,855 --> 00:59:52,522
Contention is...

735
00:59:52,524 --> 00:59:55,625
80 miles back
the other way.

736
00:59:55,627 --> 00:59:58,027
We'd have to about kill
our horses.

737
00:59:58,029 --> 00:59:59,396
So we'll buy new ones.

738
00:59:59,398 --> 01:00:00,797
Charlie...

739
01:00:00,799 --> 01:00:03,065
it's his own fault
he got caught.

740
01:00:03,067 --> 01:00:04,501
He made a mistake.

741
01:00:06,637 --> 01:00:09,305
You think you could do a
better job leading this crew?

742
01:00:09,307 --> 01:00:10,239
Maybe.

743
01:00:13,210 --> 01:00:14,611
[COCKS GUN]

744
01:00:17,064 --> 01:00:19,633
You forgotten
what he done for us.

745
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:28,375
We're going
to Contention.

746
01:00:40,871 --> 01:00:42,505
Can't say
I didn't warn you.

747
01:00:45,125 --> 01:00:47,693
There's a shortcut
we could take.

748
01:00:47,695 --> 01:00:49,512
Shortcut?

749
01:00:49,514 --> 01:00:51,047
Through the pass.

750
01:00:51,049 --> 01:00:52,515
Takes you right through
to Contention.

751
01:00:52,517 --> 01:00:54,517
Why didn't you say
something before?

752
01:00:54,519 --> 01:00:56,786
That's Apache country.

753
01:00:56,788 --> 01:00:58,788
BUTTERFIELD: I thought the
government gave them land.

754
01:00:58,790 --> 01:01:00,089
These are the ones
refused to go.

755
01:01:00,091 --> 01:01:01,724
I wouldn't take
that pass.

756
01:01:01,726 --> 01:01:03,459
Oh, you'd like us
to take the long way?

757
01:01:03,461 --> 01:01:05,728
That's right.
And let your boys catch us?

758
01:01:08,199 --> 01:01:10,133
Mr. Butterfield,

759
01:01:10,135 --> 01:01:11,600
the Apache that live
in that pass

760
01:01:11,602 --> 01:01:13,002
are the ones
that stayed to fight.

761
01:01:13,987 --> 01:01:15,504
They enjoy killing.

762
01:01:15,506 --> 01:01:17,924
You ain't gonna make it.

763
01:01:21,495 --> 01:01:23,163
We'll take our chances.

764
01:01:51,808 --> 01:01:53,609
Something on your mind, Dan?

765
01:01:55,346 --> 01:01:57,580
Why'd you kill Tucker?

766
01:01:57,582 --> 01:01:59,416
Why not me?

767
01:01:59,418 --> 01:02:01,151
Or Butterfield?

768
01:02:01,153 --> 01:02:03,019
Well, Tucker took
my horse.

769
01:02:05,656 --> 01:02:07,424
Did you like him, Dan?

770
01:02:07,426 --> 01:02:09,526
No.

771
01:02:09,528 --> 01:02:11,294
He told me
he burnt down your barn.

772
01:02:13,097 --> 01:02:16,166
He was an asshole...

773
01:02:16,168 --> 01:02:18,134
but wishing him dead
and killing him

774
01:02:18,136 --> 01:02:20,052
are two different things.

775
01:02:20,054 --> 01:02:22,054
Your conscience
is sensitive, Dan.

776
01:02:22,056 --> 01:02:23,956
I don't think it's
my favorite part of you.

777
01:02:25,392 --> 01:02:27,477
Button it up, Mr. Wade.

778
01:02:27,479 --> 01:02:29,079
You wanna talk to somebody,

779
01:02:29,081 --> 01:02:31,397
talk to me.

780
01:02:31,399 --> 01:02:32,932
I don't like talking
to you, Byron.

781
01:02:32,934 --> 01:02:34,533
Not when I have the gun.

782
01:02:34,535 --> 01:02:36,035
No, that ain't it.

783
01:02:36,037 --> 01:02:38,221
I just don't find you
that interesting.

784
01:02:38,223 --> 01:02:39,322
[CHUCKLES]

785
01:02:39,324 --> 01:02:40,807
Laugh it up, Doc,

786
01:02:40,809 --> 01:02:42,725
till he guts you
like a fish.

787
01:02:42,727 --> 01:02:45,044
Byron's like a song
with one note.

788
01:02:45,046 --> 01:02:46,913
You ever read another book
in your life, Byron,

789
01:02:46,915 --> 01:02:48,214
besides the Bible?

790
01:02:48,216 --> 01:02:50,016
No need.

791
01:02:50,817 --> 01:02:53,135
Byron acts pious.

792
01:02:53,137 --> 01:02:54,537
Few years ago,

793
01:02:54,539 --> 01:02:56,706
when he was under
contract to Central,

794
01:02:56,708 --> 01:02:59,542
I seen him and a bunch
of other Pinks

795
01:02:59,544 --> 01:03:02,311
mow down 32 Apache women
and children.

796
01:03:02,313 --> 01:03:04,197
BYRON:
Renegades...

797
01:03:04,199 --> 01:03:06,583
gunning down railroad men
and their families.

798
01:03:06,585 --> 01:03:08,985
Picking 'em off the road
one by one.

799
01:03:08,987 --> 01:03:10,152
Scalping 'em.

800
01:03:10,154 --> 01:03:11,253
There was young ones
running around

801
01:03:11,255 --> 01:03:12,589
crying and screaming.

802
01:03:12,591 --> 01:03:15,324
No more than
three years old.

803
01:03:15,326 --> 01:03:18,327
And his boys shot 'em all
then pushed 'em into a ditch.

804
01:03:18,329 --> 01:03:19,862
Some of them
was still crying.

805
01:03:21,899 --> 01:03:25,501
But I guess Byron figured
that Jesus wouldn't mind.

806
01:03:28,005 --> 01:03:29,722
Apparently Jesus
don't like the Apache.

807
01:03:31,625 --> 01:03:34,226
Keep on talking...

808
01:03:34,228 --> 01:03:35,795
all the way to Yuma,

809
01:03:35,797 --> 01:03:37,630
right up them steps,

810
01:03:37,632 --> 01:03:39,098
to the rope,

811
01:03:39,100 --> 01:03:40,366
straight to Hell.

812
01:03:41,935 --> 01:03:44,069
Day I die, Byron,

813
01:03:44,071 --> 01:03:45,905
I'm getting sprung
from Hell.

814
01:03:45,907 --> 01:03:47,239
I might feel the same,

815
01:03:47,241 --> 01:03:48,708
if I come from the seed

816
01:03:48,710 --> 01:03:50,910
of a drunk gravedigger

817
01:03:50,912 --> 01:03:53,212
and the rancid womb
of a whore.

818
01:04:06,043 --> 01:04:07,560
Drop it, Dan Evans.

819
01:04:07,562 --> 01:04:08,928
Drop it.

820
01:04:08,930 --> 01:04:11,397
Toss that
to the ground, Doc.

821
01:04:11,399 --> 01:04:13,165
Mr. Butterfield.

822
01:04:16,570 --> 01:04:18,505
Now I believe, Dan,

823
01:04:18,507 --> 01:04:20,339
you're carrying
a pistol as well.

824
01:04:20,341 --> 01:04:22,074
I'd appreciate it
if you take that out

825
01:04:22,076 --> 01:04:23,092
and drop it
on the ground.

826
01:04:23,094 --> 01:04:24,093
Thank you.

827
01:04:30,350 --> 01:04:32,101
Now, I always
liked you, Byron.

828
01:04:32,103 --> 01:04:33,686
[GRUNTS]

829
01:04:33,688 --> 01:04:35,287
But you never knew
when to shut up.

830
01:04:38,942 --> 01:04:41,727
Even bad men
love their mamas.

831
01:04:43,013 --> 01:04:45,297
[THUD]

832
01:04:47,334 --> 01:04:50,603
Now I think it's time
for everybody to go home.

833
01:04:50,605 --> 01:04:52,772
Don't you move,
Mr. Wade.

834
01:04:52,774 --> 01:04:55,474
Let go of that shotgun.

835
01:04:55,476 --> 01:04:57,276
William...

836
01:04:57,278 --> 01:04:58,928
what the hell
are you doing here?

837
01:04:58,930 --> 01:05:01,097
Now, I don't think
you gonna shoot a man

838
01:05:01,099 --> 01:05:02,699
you admire in the back
of the head, boy.

839
01:05:04,702 --> 01:05:08,370
Dan, tell your boy
it's over.

840
01:05:08,372 --> 01:05:11,474
You think you can keep
your gun on him, William?

841
01:05:11,476 --> 01:05:14,227
I'm doing a damn sight
better than you did.

842
01:06:01,041 --> 01:06:02,975
You ever been
to Dodge City?

843
01:06:07,013 --> 01:06:08,281
No.

844
01:06:09,717 --> 01:06:11,818
Stop talking to him.

845
01:06:15,672 --> 01:06:17,107
The way you're shuffling
those cards,

846
01:06:17,109 --> 01:06:18,992
I took you for a pro.

847
01:06:20,060 --> 01:06:21,543
I practice a lot.

848
01:06:21,545 --> 01:06:23,563
I can tell.

849
01:06:30,487 --> 01:06:32,405
You ever been
to Dodge?

850
01:06:32,407 --> 01:06:34,490
Yes, indeed.

851
01:06:34,492 --> 01:06:37,059
Meanest, most beautiful
dirty city there ever was.

852
01:06:37,061 --> 01:06:39,311
Saloon was just overflowing

853
01:06:39,313 --> 01:06:41,063
with cattle drivers,
and road agents,

854
01:06:41,065 --> 01:06:42,598
prospectors, gunslingers,

855
01:06:42,600 --> 01:06:44,249
gamblers, and women.

856
01:06:47,154 --> 01:06:51,123
Women who'll do things to you
you'll never forget.

857
01:06:51,125 --> 01:06:53,492
They'll give you a disease
you'll never forget.

858
01:06:53,494 --> 01:06:55,161
Money in your pocket
in Dodge City,

859
01:06:55,163 --> 01:06:57,547
you can have everything
a man ever wished for.

860
01:06:59,833 --> 01:07:01,567
Everything a man
comes to need.

861
01:07:04,971 --> 01:07:09,108
I got there on my own as a boy
not much bigger than you.

862
01:07:09,110 --> 01:07:12,078
And how many men you killed
since then, Wade?

863
01:07:14,665 --> 01:07:16,749
How many families
you destroyed?

864
01:07:21,054 --> 01:07:22,855
Quite a few.

865
01:07:25,608 --> 01:07:27,076
Is it true
that you dynamited

866
01:07:27,078 --> 01:07:29,595
a wagon full of prospectors
in the Western Territories

867
01:07:29,597 --> 01:07:31,548
last spring?

868
01:07:31,550 --> 01:07:33,015
No, that's a lie.

869
01:07:33,017 --> 01:07:35,284
It was a train full.

870
01:07:44,378 --> 01:07:46,763
Well, Dan...

871
01:07:46,765 --> 01:07:49,182
[SIGHS]

872
01:07:49,184 --> 01:07:50,566
I gotta take a piss.

873
01:07:52,836 --> 01:07:54,887
You know, I thought
he was gonna shoot me

874
01:07:54,889 --> 01:07:56,055
back at the ravine.

875
01:07:57,557 --> 01:07:59,225
I really thought
he was gonna do it.

876
01:07:59,227 --> 01:08:01,227
You know, there's
a wildness in his eyes.

877
01:08:01,229 --> 01:08:03,496
It reminds me of--
He's gonna be nothing like you, Wade.

878
01:08:09,569 --> 01:08:12,338
William's got a head start
on the path of decency.

879
01:08:14,675 --> 01:08:16,275
Yeah, that's why
I don't mess around

880
01:08:16,277 --> 01:08:17,977
with doing
anything good, Dan.

881
01:08:22,332 --> 01:08:25,584
You do one good deed
for somebody...

882
01:08:25,586 --> 01:08:27,437
I imagine
it's habit-forming.

883
01:08:29,056 --> 01:08:31,357
Something decent.

884
01:08:31,359 --> 01:08:33,359
See that grateful look
in their eyes,

885
01:08:33,361 --> 01:08:35,428
imagine it makes you feel
like Christ Hisself.

886
01:08:35,430 --> 01:08:37,647
All right, I had enough
of this, Wade.

887
01:08:37,649 --> 01:08:39,248
Come on, let's go.

888
01:08:43,937 --> 01:08:45,071
Shh.

889
01:08:52,346 --> 01:08:54,380
[GUNSHOTS]

890
01:08:54,382 --> 01:08:56,648
[GRUNTS]

891
01:09:08,361 --> 01:09:09,078
William!

892
01:09:33,854 --> 01:09:35,221
There's three of 'em.
Yours?

893
01:09:35,223 --> 01:09:37,323
If they were mine,
you'd be dead.

894
01:09:40,594 --> 01:09:42,344
Give me that gun, Wade.

895
01:09:44,097 --> 01:09:45,497
Wade?

896
01:09:45,499 --> 01:09:46,598
Wade!

897
01:09:46,600 --> 01:09:48,334
[BULLETS WHIZZING]

898
01:09:54,574 --> 01:09:55,507
[GUNSHOT]

899
01:10:02,065 --> 01:10:03,299
[GUNSHOT]

900
01:10:32,946 --> 01:10:35,147
I told you not to come
this way.

901
01:10:35,149 --> 01:10:36,715
It was McElroy's decision.

902
01:10:36,717 --> 01:10:39,218
I told you
there'd be trouble.

903
01:10:44,158 --> 01:10:46,358
Give me the keys
to the handcuffs.

904
01:11:10,350 --> 01:11:11,734
DOC:
Easy...

905
01:11:13,169 --> 01:11:14,386
Easy now.

906
01:11:15,672 --> 01:11:16,622
Where is he?

907
01:11:16,624 --> 01:11:19,174
He's gone.

908
01:11:19,176 --> 01:11:21,760
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

909
01:11:21,762 --> 01:11:24,697
He took the horses with him.
I found this in the grass.

910
01:11:30,204 --> 01:11:32,171
What's the quickest way
out of the pass?

911
01:11:32,173 --> 01:11:35,941
He'll be looking for help
getting his cuffs off.

912
01:11:37,344 --> 01:11:39,878
We're going after him?

913
01:11:39,880 --> 01:11:41,347
Well, there ain't no reward

914
01:11:41,349 --> 01:11:43,482
for getting him halfway
to that train, is there?

915
01:11:56,296 --> 01:11:57,663
[DISTANT EXPLOSION]

916
01:12:02,485 --> 01:12:03,719
[MEN CHATTERING IN DISTANCE]

917
01:12:03,721 --> 01:12:05,121
[EXPLOSION]

918
01:12:29,145 --> 01:12:32,615
[MEN AND WOMEN CHATTERING IN CHINESE]

919
01:12:54,854 --> 01:12:57,123
[DISTANT EXPLOSION]

920
01:12:57,125 --> 01:12:58,790
I got to be honest
with y'all.

921
01:12:58,792 --> 01:13:00,759
I like some of their food.

922
01:13:00,761 --> 01:13:03,195
As for wanting
$40 a month now

923
01:13:03,197 --> 01:13:05,097
like them Irish up north--

924
01:13:05,099 --> 01:13:06,965
[WOMAN SPEAKING CHINESE]

925
01:13:06,967 --> 01:13:08,767
Goddamn Coolies.

926
01:13:08,769 --> 01:13:11,470
They'll work just fine with
my left boot up their ass.

927
01:13:11,472 --> 01:13:14,039
Well, if could teach
a monkey to lay track--

928
01:13:14,041 --> 01:13:16,242
Well, what we need
is some Negroes

929
01:13:16,244 --> 01:13:17,909
brung in here,
Mr. Boles.

930
01:13:17,911 --> 01:13:19,077
Show these Chinamen

931
01:13:19,079 --> 01:13:20,412
what real work is.

932
01:13:20,414 --> 01:13:22,181
[CHITTERING]

933
01:13:28,388 --> 01:13:30,690
Holy Christ.

934
01:13:32,326 --> 01:13:35,761
Who's that?
That's him.

935
01:13:38,882 --> 01:13:40,916
You, help me
with the handcuffs.

936
01:13:40,918 --> 01:13:41,851
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

937
01:13:43,186 --> 01:13:44,553
Break the chain.

938
01:13:44,555 --> 01:13:46,455
Use the hammer.
Break the chain.

939
01:13:46,457 --> 01:13:47,739
[GUNSHOTS]

940
01:13:49,626 --> 01:13:53,045
MAN: I got five guns on
you out here, Ben Wade!

941
01:13:53,047 --> 01:13:54,697
Best come on out!

942
01:14:13,783 --> 01:14:14,883
Our horses.

943
01:14:20,256 --> 01:14:22,692
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

944
01:14:22,694 --> 01:14:24,560
[PLUNGER WHIRRING]

945
01:14:37,990 --> 01:14:40,125
What in the hell's
going on here?

946
01:14:42,028 --> 01:14:45,330
Mr. Butterfield,
all finished in Bisbee?

947
01:14:45,332 --> 01:14:47,332
Mr. Boles.

948
01:14:54,974 --> 01:14:58,794
Better hurry. We're making the last
blasts through the mountains this week.

949
01:14:58,796 --> 01:15:00,395
That's my prisoner.

950
01:15:00,397 --> 01:15:01,930
I'm taking him
to Contention,

951
01:15:01,932 --> 01:15:04,416
putting him on
the prison train to Yuma.

952
01:15:04,418 --> 01:15:06,468
What prisoner?

953
01:15:06,470 --> 01:15:08,370
Come now, Mr. Boles,

954
01:15:08,372 --> 01:15:09,905
that's Ben Wade
you have there.

955
01:15:09,907 --> 01:15:13,342
Ben Wade gunned down
my kid brother

956
01:15:13,344 --> 01:15:14,810
in front of me

957
01:15:14,812 --> 01:15:17,313
six years ago in Abilene.

958
01:15:17,315 --> 01:15:20,065
Your brother was a lyin',
bilkin' card sharp.

959
01:15:23,520 --> 01:15:26,254
That is, if he's
the asshole I remember.

960
01:15:26,256 --> 01:15:28,958
Could, of course, been some other
asshole I killed that I forgot about.

961
01:15:31,194 --> 01:15:32,695
[PLUNGER WHIRRS]
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLES]

962
01:15:34,030 --> 01:15:34,964
[STIFLED GROAN]

963
01:15:44,223 --> 01:15:45,858
You can't do that.
That's immoral.

964
01:15:45,860 --> 01:15:47,359
[PLUNGER WHIRRS]

965
01:15:47,361 --> 01:15:49,127
[ELECTRICITY STOPS]

966
01:15:49,129 --> 01:15:51,029
Moral ain't got
a damn thing to do with it.

967
01:15:56,520 --> 01:15:59,855
I was expecting to collect
a $200 reward for that man.

968
01:16:01,791 --> 01:16:04,059
I'm delivering him
to Contention.

969
01:16:04,061 --> 01:16:05,895
I need that money.

970
01:16:05,897 --> 01:16:08,163
Need it bad enough
to die?

971
01:16:18,224 --> 01:16:21,760
Well, at least let us
take our horses.

972
01:16:21,762 --> 01:16:24,063
I got no problem
with that...

973
01:16:24,065 --> 01:16:26,665
as long as you
ride away, mister.

974
01:16:26,667 --> 01:16:28,667
Nice knowing you, Dan.

975
01:16:35,809 --> 01:16:37,559
Yah!

976
01:17:09,676 --> 01:17:12,178
Did you see me get that one
with the shovel?

977
01:17:12,180 --> 01:17:13,729
[GUNSHOTS]
[GRUNTS]

978
01:17:13,731 --> 01:17:14,964
Doc.

979
01:17:14,966 --> 01:17:16,131
Doc!

980
01:17:16,133 --> 01:17:17,483
[GUNSHOTS]

981
01:17:29,613 --> 01:17:30,813
Dan!

982
01:17:43,877 --> 01:17:45,928
[HORSES NEIGHING]

983
01:17:50,133 --> 01:17:51,399
Goddamn it!

984
01:18:06,516 --> 01:18:09,100
Did we make it?

985
01:18:09,102 --> 01:18:11,270
Did we get away?

986
01:18:11,272 --> 01:18:12,371
Yeah, Doc.

987
01:18:13,356 --> 01:18:14,573
We did.

988
01:18:15,792 --> 01:18:16,792
Thanks to you.

989
01:18:42,034 --> 01:18:44,135
We need a place
to lay low.

990
01:18:44,137 --> 01:18:46,371
Keep him outta sight
till the train comes.

991
01:18:47,973 --> 01:18:50,141
There's a hotel up here.

992
01:18:50,143 --> 01:18:52,076
I'll check us in.
You ride around back.

993
01:18:52,078 --> 01:18:53,729
All right.
Follow me.

994
01:18:59,218 --> 01:19:00,468
Hello, gentlemen.

995
01:19:02,238 --> 01:19:04,456
Hey, William, you go keep
a watch at the railhead.

996
01:19:04,458 --> 01:19:06,041
If you see them coming--

997
01:19:06,043 --> 01:19:07,476
I'll let you know.

998
01:19:08,811 --> 01:19:10,012
And William?

999
01:19:27,363 --> 01:19:29,915
There's a Can-Can on the hour
if you're interested.

1000
01:19:49,168 --> 01:19:51,269
It's the bridal suite.

1001
01:19:51,271 --> 01:19:53,205
Hope you don't mind.
It's all they had.

1002
01:20:07,887 --> 01:20:10,105
Well, well.

1003
01:20:10,107 --> 01:20:14,310
That looks like
rain clouds over Bisbee.

1004
01:20:14,312 --> 01:20:16,228
You still need
that $200, Dan?

1005
01:20:16,230 --> 01:20:17,663
Shut up.

1006
01:20:19,632 --> 01:20:23,986
Mr. Evans, you continue
to give me great confidence.

1007
01:20:23,988 --> 01:20:26,188
DAN:
Well, it ain't 3:10 yet.

1008
01:20:26,190 --> 01:20:28,157
I'm gonna go see
about the marshal.

1009
01:20:32,095 --> 01:20:33,945
Come on, move.
Let's go.

1010
01:20:46,659 --> 01:20:49,911
We're looking for a group
escorting an outlaw

1011
01:20:49,913 --> 01:20:51,847
by the name of Ben Wade.

1012
01:20:51,849 --> 01:20:54,315
Yeah, we been chasing him
through these tunnels.

1013
01:20:59,839 --> 01:21:01,724
Who are you?

1014
01:21:01,726 --> 01:21:02,791
What's it to you?

1015
01:21:04,194 --> 01:21:06,695
Ben Wade killed
my brother.

1016
01:21:06,697 --> 01:21:08,964
Then your brother
must be famous.

1017
01:21:10,432 --> 01:21:14,936
You boys some kind
of posse?

1018
01:21:27,867 --> 01:21:30,002
I hate posses.

1019
01:21:30,004 --> 01:21:31,453
[TICKING]

1020
01:21:34,207 --> 01:21:36,040
[HORSE NEIGHS IN DISTANCE]

1021
01:21:37,943 --> 01:21:40,945
So this is
the bridal suite.

1022
01:21:40,947 --> 01:21:43,665
Now, I wonder
how many brides

1023
01:21:43,667 --> 01:21:44,849
have taken in this view.

1024
01:21:44,851 --> 01:21:47,102
[CHUCKLING]

1025
01:21:48,988 --> 01:21:51,306
What are you gonna do
with your $200 now, Dan?

1026
01:21:51,308 --> 01:21:52,824
Now that the rains
are coming?

1027
01:21:52,826 --> 01:21:56,078
[SIGHS]
I owe people money, Wade.

1028
01:21:56,080 --> 01:21:58,080
That drought left me
in the hole.

1029
01:22:01,084 --> 01:22:02,901
Well, what do you think
about double that amount?

1030
01:22:04,604 --> 01:22:06,738
You could pay your debts,

1031
01:22:06,740 --> 01:22:09,308
buy a hundred more cows,

1032
01:22:09,310 --> 01:22:10,943
build a new barn.

1033
01:22:10,945 --> 01:22:12,728
How you reckon
I'm gonna do that?

1034
01:22:15,532 --> 01:22:17,616
Just lay down your gun
and let me walk out the door.

1035
01:22:17,618 --> 01:22:21,119
It's worth $400 to me.

1036
01:22:21,121 --> 01:22:22,754
Is that what you reckon
my price is?

1037
01:22:23,990 --> 01:22:25,590
No.

1038
01:22:27,660 --> 01:22:30,062
No, I reckon
it's a thousand.

1039
01:22:30,064 --> 01:22:32,197
$1,000.

1040
01:22:32,199 --> 01:22:33,732
Now, there's 10 times
that amount

1041
01:22:33,734 --> 01:22:35,533
in Butterfield's coach.
Oh, yeah?

1042
01:22:35,535 --> 01:22:37,602
You want my cut, Dan?
[CHUCKLES]

1043
01:22:37,604 --> 01:22:39,972
It's all yours.

1044
01:22:39,974 --> 01:22:42,808
Isn't that kind of reckless
of you, Wade?

1045
01:22:42,810 --> 01:22:44,492
Seeing as, uh...

1046
01:22:44,494 --> 01:22:46,161
you're so sure that, uh,

1047
01:22:46,163 --> 01:22:48,363
your crew's coming
to get you?

1048
01:22:49,215 --> 01:22:50,749
Oh, they're coming, Dan.

1049
01:22:52,318 --> 01:22:54,920
Sure as God's vengeance,
they're coming.

1050
01:22:57,824 --> 01:22:59,441
But I just like
to do things easy.

1051
01:23:02,145 --> 01:23:05,347
Imagine what you could do
with a thousand dollars, Dan.

1052
01:23:05,349 --> 01:23:06,798
You could hire
a couple of ranch hands.

1053
01:23:06,800 --> 01:23:10,152
Your boys could go to school,
grow up smart.

1054
01:23:10,154 --> 01:23:12,504
What about Alice?

1055
01:23:12,506 --> 01:23:14,172
She would be
the proud wife

1056
01:23:14,174 --> 01:23:15,990
of a bona fide
Arizona rancher.

1057
01:23:19,094 --> 01:23:22,097
All you got to do
is say yes.

1058
01:23:26,052 --> 01:23:27,319
[LAUGHS]

1059
01:23:27,321 --> 01:23:29,588
Well...

1060
01:23:29,590 --> 01:23:31,523
would you give me
a bank note, Wade?

1061
01:23:31,525 --> 01:23:35,260
Or maybe you'd be kind enough
to make a deposit for me.

1062
01:23:35,262 --> 01:23:36,511
Cash.

1063
01:23:41,734 --> 01:23:43,068
Well, you--
you tell me, Wade.

1064
01:23:43,070 --> 01:23:46,054
How would I account for--

1065
01:23:46,056 --> 01:23:48,823
for that amount of money?

1066
01:23:48,825 --> 01:23:52,110
And what would I tell people
when I spend it?

1067
01:23:52,112 --> 01:23:54,045
That, uh--

1068
01:23:54,047 --> 01:23:55,430
That you got the jump on me,

1069
01:23:55,432 --> 01:23:59,518
you escaped,
and somehow I got a fortune?

1070
01:23:59,520 --> 01:24:00,635
Hmm?

1071
01:24:00,637 --> 01:24:02,070
[LAUGHING]

1072
01:24:02,072 --> 01:24:04,539
No. How dumb do you think
people are?

1073
01:24:04,541 --> 01:24:07,526
Nobody needs to know.

1074
01:24:11,130 --> 01:24:12,230
You know what?

1075
01:24:12,232 --> 01:24:14,816
Would you do me a favor?

1076
01:24:14,818 --> 01:24:17,368
Don't talk to me for a while.

1077
01:24:17,370 --> 01:24:19,604
You mean we're still
not friends?

1078
01:24:19,606 --> 01:24:21,056
No.

1079
01:24:23,593 --> 01:24:25,394
No, we're not.

1080
01:24:25,396 --> 01:24:27,496
[CHUCKLES]
Come five minutes to three,

1081
01:24:27,498 --> 01:24:29,881
we're gonna be a hell of a
lot closer than you think.

1082
01:24:38,825 --> 01:24:41,493
♪ They're gonna hang me ♪

1083
01:24:41,495 --> 01:24:43,478
♪ In the mornin' ♪

1084
01:24:45,214 --> 01:24:47,098
♪ Before the night is done ♪

1085
01:24:48,784 --> 01:24:51,653
♪ They're gonna hang me ♪

1086
01:24:51,655 --> 01:24:53,555
♪ In the mornin' ♪

1087
01:24:55,441 --> 01:24:57,893
♪ I'll never see the sun ♪

1088
01:24:57,895 --> 01:24:59,344
[TICKING]

1089
01:25:09,772 --> 01:25:10,805
[KNOCKING]

1090
01:25:13,576 --> 01:25:14,743
Who is it?

1091
01:25:14,745 --> 01:25:16,511
It's me, Dan.

1092
01:25:16,513 --> 01:25:18,530
I brought help.

1093
01:25:18,532 --> 01:25:22,016
You been gone a long time,
Mr. Butterfield.

1094
01:25:22,018 --> 01:25:26,121
How do I know somebody ain't
got a gun on you out there?

1095
01:25:26,123 --> 01:25:27,822
[METAL SLIDING]

1096
01:25:40,485 --> 01:25:43,855
Dan, this is
Marshal Will Doane.

1097
01:25:43,857 --> 01:25:45,957
Marshal.
Mr. Evans.

1098
01:25:48,961 --> 01:25:51,963
Two of my finest men:
Harvey Pell...

1099
01:25:54,550 --> 01:25:56,217
Sam Fuller.

1100
01:25:56,219 --> 01:25:58,219
I'm sorry about
all that, Marshal.

1101
01:25:58,221 --> 01:26:00,355
I really am grateful for the help.
Don't mention it.

1102
01:26:00,357 --> 01:26:03,074
So you fellas really gonna
help put me on this train?

1103
01:26:05,194 --> 01:26:08,196
It may not seem
like it, Mr. Wade,

1104
01:26:08,198 --> 01:26:10,164
but we got law and order
in this town,

1105
01:26:10,166 --> 01:26:13,067
just like any other.
Well, that's very reassuring, Marshal.

1106
01:26:14,570 --> 01:26:17,255
How much is Butterfield
paying you?

1107
01:26:17,257 --> 01:26:19,240
That's none of your business.

1108
01:26:19,242 --> 01:26:20,641
You gonna come with us?

1109
01:26:20,643 --> 01:26:23,194
Oh, I'll be walking
with you...

1110
01:26:23,196 --> 01:26:26,831
every step of the way.

1111
01:26:26,833 --> 01:26:28,566
You have my word
on that, Dan.

1112
01:26:28,568 --> 01:26:31,219
So there's five of us.
Five is good.

1113
01:26:31,221 --> 01:26:33,822
[WADE CHUCKLING]

1114
01:26:33,824 --> 01:26:35,523
It ain't enough.

1115
01:26:36,926 --> 01:26:38,894
It ain't nearly enough.

1116
01:27:01,266 --> 01:27:02,384
[KNOCKING]

1117
01:27:02,386 --> 01:27:04,118
Pa!
That's my boy.

1118
01:27:07,289 --> 01:27:08,223
They're coming.

1119
01:27:09,792 --> 01:27:12,043
They're coming this way.
I seen 'em.

1120
01:27:12,045 --> 01:27:14,745
Where?
About a mile out. Same way we come.

1121
01:27:14,747 --> 01:27:17,515
How many are there?
Seven. Eight.

1122
01:27:17,517 --> 01:27:19,133
Which is it, boy?
Seven or eight?

1123
01:27:21,320 --> 01:27:23,037
Seven.

1124
01:27:27,059 --> 01:27:29,194
Yah! Yah!

1125
01:27:34,650 --> 01:27:36,000
Folks, sorry to bother you,

1126
01:27:36,002 --> 01:27:38,052
but I'm gonna need you all
to move outside

1127
01:27:38,054 --> 01:27:39,320
as quickly as possible.

1128
01:27:39,322 --> 01:27:40,822
That's it, folks.

1129
01:27:40,824 --> 01:27:42,424
Thank you very much.

1130
01:27:42,426 --> 01:27:44,091
That's it.
Move along, folks.

1131
01:27:44,093 --> 01:27:46,127
Move along.

1132
01:27:46,129 --> 01:27:47,429
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1133
01:27:47,431 --> 01:27:48,663
MAN: 
Come on, now!

1134
01:27:48,665 --> 01:27:50,198
MAN #2: 
Hey! Get out of my way!

1135
01:27:52,367 --> 01:27:53,518
Right there.

1136
01:27:58,241 --> 01:27:59,507
[RAPPING ON DOOR]

1137
01:28:08,867 --> 01:28:10,251
[MEN LAUGHING]

1138
01:28:12,254 --> 01:28:14,789
There sure are
a lot of 'em.

1139
01:28:14,791 --> 01:28:17,075
FULLER: I didn't figure on
it being the whole gang.

1140
01:28:42,334 --> 01:28:43,267
Boss.

1141
01:28:44,469 --> 01:28:45,436
Boss?

1142
01:28:47,873 --> 01:28:48,924
Boss, you in there?

1143
01:28:50,293 --> 01:28:53,044
What do you want me
to tell him?

1144
01:28:53,046 --> 01:28:55,981
You tell him you'll write him
a letter every day from Yuma.

1145
01:29:03,990 --> 01:29:06,191
You be careful, Wade.

1146
01:29:11,414 --> 01:29:13,214
Charlie. Boys.

1147
01:29:13,216 --> 01:29:15,216
MEN: Boss. Hey, Boss.
Yeah.

1148
01:29:15,218 --> 01:29:17,285
Charlie, why don't you
take the boys

1149
01:29:17,287 --> 01:29:18,737
down to the saloon
and buy 'em a drink.

1150
01:29:21,374 --> 01:29:22,874
You okay?

1151
01:29:22,876 --> 01:29:24,859
Oh, I'm fine.

1152
01:29:24,861 --> 01:29:26,968
I'm just sittin' up here
with my four new friends.

1153
01:29:26,994 --> 01:29:27,520
Hey...

1154
01:29:28,948 --> 01:29:30,548
that's enough.

1155
01:29:35,454 --> 01:29:37,822
Thank you, Charlie.
Boys.

1156
01:29:57,109 --> 01:29:58,960
Listen up!

1157
01:29:58,962 --> 01:30:00,628
Listen up!

1158
01:30:02,698 --> 01:30:05,867
That's Ben Wade
they have up there.

1159
01:30:05,869 --> 01:30:07,585
Ben...Wade!

1160
01:30:13,425 --> 01:30:14,459
Now...

1161
01:30:14,461 --> 01:30:18,096
the Railroad intends...

1162
01:30:19,748 --> 01:30:23,651
to put him on
the 3:10 to Yuma...

1163
01:30:23,653 --> 01:30:25,486
and hang him.

1164
01:30:25,488 --> 01:30:26,955
What's he doing?

1165
01:30:33,328 --> 01:30:38,249
We will give you
200 cash dollars

1166
01:30:38,251 --> 01:30:40,785
to any man who shoots

1167
01:30:40,787 --> 01:30:42,720
any one of his captors.
MAN: How much?

1168
01:30:44,423 --> 01:30:49,461
200 cash dollars
guaranteed!

1169
01:30:53,432 --> 01:30:57,968
$200 guaranteed!

1170
01:30:57,970 --> 01:30:59,870
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1171
01:30:59,872 --> 01:31:01,506
Right here. You got me.
Hand it over.

1172
01:31:01,508 --> 01:31:02,773
I'll tell you now,
mister.

1173
01:31:02,775 --> 01:31:04,542
I'll take 200.
Give me the money.

1174
01:31:04,544 --> 01:31:05,810
Well, you gotta
shoot 'em first.

1175
01:31:12,784 --> 01:31:15,236
There's gotta be 30, 40
more guns out there now.

1176
01:31:17,223 --> 01:31:19,023
Oh, to hell with this.

1177
01:31:20,509 --> 01:31:23,377
Now just a minute, Marshal.
Look, look.

1178
01:31:23,379 --> 01:31:24,779
If it's a fair fight,
well, sure.

1179
01:31:24,781 --> 01:31:26,664
I'd stay for that.

1180
01:31:26,666 --> 01:31:27,599
A fair fight, that--

1181
01:31:30,536 --> 01:31:32,570
That's a man's duty,
but...

1182
01:31:32,572 --> 01:31:34,472
there's only five
of us.

1183
01:31:36,508 --> 01:31:37,708
I'm sorry, mister,

1184
01:31:37,710 --> 01:31:39,910
but I'm not gonna
die here today.

1185
01:31:43,516 --> 01:31:44,749
And neither are my men.

1186
01:31:44,751 --> 01:31:45,867
Marshal...

1187
01:31:49,137 --> 01:31:50,137
forgot this.

1188
01:31:55,861 --> 01:31:58,013
Marshal--

1189
01:31:58,015 --> 01:32:00,464
Marshal!
Marshal, what's the--

1190
01:32:02,835 --> 01:32:03,868
[SIGHS]

1191
01:32:03,870 --> 01:32:06,170
Now, you see, Dan...

1192
01:32:06,172 --> 01:32:11,109
generally, pretty much
everyone wants to live.

1193
01:32:11,111 --> 01:32:14,011
I'll double your money.
Let's go, boys.

1194
01:32:14,013 --> 01:32:17,047
Please. Do you wanna see us
shot down in the street?

1195
01:32:17,049 --> 01:32:18,616
This thing happened
in Bisbee.

1196
01:32:18,618 --> 01:32:20,518
That means
Butterfield, too.

1197
01:32:20,520 --> 01:32:22,187
Why bring your troubles
to Contention?

1198
01:32:22,189 --> 01:32:25,072
We've got families.
Every one of us is a family man.

1199
01:32:25,074 --> 01:32:26,741
I'm a family man, too.

1200
01:32:26,743 --> 01:32:29,677
He's gonna walk out
on you.

1201
01:32:29,679 --> 01:32:33,231
Then you best get out
like the rest of us.

1202
01:32:37,569 --> 01:32:40,571
WADE: He's gonna
comeback up here,

1203
01:32:40,573 --> 01:32:42,606
and he's gonna
walk out on you.

1204
01:32:42,608 --> 01:32:46,110
Now what you gotta figure
is why you and your boy

1205
01:32:46,112 --> 01:32:48,362
are gonna die.

1206
01:32:51,283 --> 01:32:53,852
Because Butterfield's railroad
lost some money?

1207
01:33:12,654 --> 01:33:15,890
[GUNSHOTS]

1208
01:33:24,132 --> 01:33:25,983
Is that all of 'em?

1209
01:33:25,985 --> 01:33:27,702
MAN: Get inside!
MAN #2: Get a doctor!

1210
01:33:30,622 --> 01:33:31,689
Almost.

1211
01:33:34,576 --> 01:33:35,593
Your move, General.

1212
01:33:40,315 --> 01:33:42,266
What do you
expect him to say?

1213
01:33:42,268 --> 01:33:45,320
I expect him to say
something that makes sense.

1214
01:33:45,322 --> 01:33:47,255
Something that might
save the two of you.

1215
01:33:47,257 --> 01:33:48,289
Take a look, Dan.

1216
01:33:50,375 --> 01:33:51,826
What's the matter?
You don't wanna see?

1217
01:33:51,828 --> 01:33:54,461
I'll see 'em soon enough.

1218
01:33:54,463 --> 01:33:56,130
What about you, kid?
You wanna look?

1219
01:33:56,132 --> 01:33:57,731
You stay away from
the window, William.

1220
01:33:57,733 --> 01:34:00,501
WADE:
Go on, take a look.

1221
01:34:00,503 --> 01:34:02,820
Animals, all of 'em.

1222
01:34:02,822 --> 01:34:05,657
Campos, stand there.
Jackson, back door.

1223
01:34:08,460 --> 01:34:10,044
They're gonna kill you
and your father, William.

1224
01:34:13,498 --> 01:34:16,183
They're gonna laugh
while they do it.

1225
01:34:16,185 --> 01:34:17,485
I think you know that.

1226
01:34:17,487 --> 01:34:19,253
Call 'em off.

1227
01:34:21,222 --> 01:34:22,890
Why should I?

1228
01:34:22,892 --> 01:34:24,609
Because you're not
all bad.

1229
01:34:29,498 --> 01:34:31,248
Yes, I am.

1230
01:34:31,250 --> 01:34:32,684
You saved us
from those Indians.

1231
01:34:32,686 --> 01:34:34,418
I saved myself.

1232
01:34:34,420 --> 01:34:35,587
You got us
through the tunnels.

1233
01:34:35,589 --> 01:34:37,188
You helped us
get away.

1234
01:34:37,190 --> 01:34:40,224
If I'd had a gun
in them tunnels,

1235
01:34:40,226 --> 01:34:42,110
I would have
used it on you.

1236
01:34:46,098 --> 01:34:47,398
I don't believe you.

1237
01:34:47,400 --> 01:34:49,884
Kid, I wouldn't last
five minutes

1238
01:34:49,886 --> 01:34:51,252
leading an outfit
like that

1239
01:34:51,254 --> 01:34:52,787
if I wasn't
as rotten as hell.

1240
01:34:54,589 --> 01:34:56,490
[WATCH TICKING]

1241
01:35:07,236 --> 01:35:08,919
[CONTINUES TICKING]

1242
01:35:13,509 --> 01:35:15,059
Dan?

1243
01:35:23,735 --> 01:35:25,786
I can't do it, Dan.

1244
01:35:25,788 --> 01:35:28,473
And if I can't do it,
you shouldn't do it, either.

1245
01:35:30,025 --> 01:35:32,860
They say discretion
is the better part of valor.

1246
01:35:32,862 --> 01:35:34,729
BUTTERFIELD: If you think
you have an obligation to me

1247
01:35:34,731 --> 01:35:37,965
or to the Railroad,
I assure you you do not.

1248
01:35:37,967 --> 01:35:39,550
I'm releasing you.

1249
01:35:39,552 --> 01:35:41,736
It's just you left, Dan.

1250
01:35:41,738 --> 01:35:43,637
Just you and your boy.

1251
01:35:43,639 --> 01:35:46,473
Maybe he's right, Pa.
Maybe we should go home.

1252
01:35:54,984 --> 01:35:58,619
Well, what did Doc Potter
give his life for, William?

1253
01:35:58,621 --> 01:36:00,054
And McElroy?

1254
01:36:00,056 --> 01:36:02,123
WADE:
Little red ants on a hill.

1255
01:36:02,125 --> 01:36:04,725
BUTTERFIELD: I'll pay you the 200,
Dan, right now,

1256
01:36:04,727 --> 01:36:05,760
and you can walk away.

1257
01:36:11,233 --> 01:36:13,768
You know,
this whole ride,

1258
01:36:13,770 --> 01:36:15,503
that's been
nagging on me.

1259
01:36:18,107 --> 01:36:21,693
That's what the government
gave me for my leg.

1260
01:36:21,695 --> 01:36:24,028
$198.36.

1261
01:36:24,030 --> 01:36:26,513
And the funny thing
is that...

1262
01:36:26,515 --> 01:36:30,034
when you think about it,
which I have been lately,

1263
01:36:30,036 --> 01:36:34,188
was they weren't paying me
to walk away.

1264
01:36:34,190 --> 01:36:36,940
They were paying me
so they could walk away.

1265
01:36:39,094 --> 01:36:41,262
Don't muddy the past
and the present, Dan.

1266
01:36:41,264 --> 01:36:42,446
No, no, no, Wade.

1267
01:36:42,448 --> 01:36:45,449
I'm seeing the world
the way it is.

1268
01:36:45,451 --> 01:36:48,352
If you take him to the train,
Pa, I'm going with you.

1269
01:36:48,354 --> 01:36:52,039
No, Mr. Butterfield's
gonna take you home.

1270
01:36:52,041 --> 01:36:54,041
No, I'm not going anywhere with him.
Yes, you are.

1271
01:36:54,043 --> 01:36:56,043
I'm staying here
with you.

1272
01:36:56,045 --> 01:36:58,779
You're gonna hold up
in a room across the hall.

1273
01:36:58,781 --> 01:37:00,464
You're gonna wait
until we leave.

1274
01:37:00,466 --> 01:37:02,816
I'll get him to Bisbee, Dan.
I promise you.

1275
01:37:02,818 --> 01:37:05,819
Oh, you're gonna promise me a lot
more than that, Butterfield.

1276
01:37:05,821 --> 01:37:09,190
I want guarantees
that Hollander

1277
01:37:09,192 --> 01:37:10,958
and his boys

1278
01:37:10,960 --> 01:37:14,195
will never set foot
on my land again,

1279
01:37:14,197 --> 01:37:15,663
and that my water's
gonna flow.

1280
01:37:15,665 --> 01:37:18,532
And I expect you
to hand my wife

1281
01:37:18,534 --> 01:37:20,335
1,000 cash dollars
when you see her.

1282
01:37:20,337 --> 01:37:22,053
You got money to spare.

1283
01:37:22,055 --> 01:37:24,388
I can deliver that.

1284
01:37:24,390 --> 01:37:25,873
Just get him on the train.

1285
01:37:28,093 --> 01:37:29,159
You heard him?

1286
01:37:29,161 --> 01:37:31,128
I heard him.

1287
01:37:33,181 --> 01:37:37,451
William, I want you to give
this back to your mother.

1288
01:37:39,521 --> 01:37:44,825
I want you to tell her that it
helped me find what was right.

1289
01:37:48,530 --> 01:37:49,664
Pa...

1290
01:37:51,432 --> 01:37:53,567
I can't.

1291
01:37:53,569 --> 01:37:55,036
I can't just leave you.

1292
01:37:55,038 --> 01:37:58,989
I'm gonna be a day
behind you, William.

1293
01:37:58,991 --> 01:38:00,591
Unless something happens,
and if it does,

1294
01:38:00,593 --> 01:38:03,610
I need a man at the ranch
to run things,

1295
01:38:03,612 --> 01:38:05,796
protect our family, and I
know that you can do that

1296
01:38:05,798 --> 01:38:08,198
because you've become
a fine man, William.

1297
01:38:08,200 --> 01:38:09,583
You've become a fine man.

1298
01:38:09,585 --> 01:38:12,453
You got all
the best parts of me.

1299
01:38:12,455 --> 01:38:13,821
What few there are.

1300
01:38:18,811 --> 01:38:20,945
And you just remember

1301
01:38:20,947 --> 01:38:22,613
that your old man

1302
01:38:22,615 --> 01:38:24,449
walked Ben Wade
to that station

1303
01:38:24,451 --> 01:38:27,301
when nobody else would.

1304
01:38:32,941 --> 01:38:34,208
[DOOR OPENS]

1305
01:38:53,578 --> 01:38:55,363
[WATCH TICKING]

1306
01:39:22,357 --> 01:39:23,490
You know,
squeezing that watch

1307
01:39:23,492 --> 01:39:25,559
won't stop time.

1308
01:39:32,768 --> 01:39:35,736
Don't get so scared.
You might back a bad move.

1309
01:39:44,179 --> 01:39:46,163
You ever read the Bible, Dan?

1310
01:39:48,383 --> 01:39:50,267
I read it one time.

1311
01:39:50,269 --> 01:39:53,203
I was eight years old.

1312
01:39:53,205 --> 01:39:55,823
My daddy just got hisself
killed over a shot of whiskey,

1313
01:39:55,825 --> 01:39:58,392
and my mama said, "We're going
back East to start over."

1314
01:40:00,279 --> 01:40:02,863
So she gave me a Bible,

1315
01:40:02,865 --> 01:40:05,115
sat me down in the train
station, told me to read it.

1316
01:40:08,386 --> 01:40:12,289
She was gonna get
our tickets.

1317
01:40:12,291 --> 01:40:15,843
Well, I did what she said.

1318
01:40:15,845 --> 01:40:18,262
I read that Bible
from cover to cover.

1319
01:40:18,264 --> 01:40:19,797
It took me three days.

1320
01:40:22,968 --> 01:40:24,301
She never came back.

1321
01:40:30,342 --> 01:40:31,959
[CHURCH BELL TOLLS]

1322
01:40:34,079 --> 01:40:35,046
[BELL TOLLS]

1323
01:40:37,782 --> 01:40:38,983
[BELL TOLLS]

1324
01:40:50,962 --> 01:40:52,329
It's time.

1325
01:41:02,223 --> 01:41:03,223
[DOOR SLAMS]

1326
01:41:03,225 --> 01:41:04,391
[LATCH CLICKS]

1327
01:41:09,181 --> 01:41:11,866
It's a half mile to the
station from here, Dan.

1328
01:41:15,571 --> 01:41:16,837
I guess we're walking.

1329
01:41:38,376 --> 01:41:39,593
There he is!

1330
01:41:45,600 --> 01:41:47,601
Go and flush him out!

1331
01:41:50,672 --> 01:41:52,706
Let's get to it!

1332
01:41:55,476 --> 01:41:56,610
Lucky.

1333
01:42:00,298 --> 01:42:01,365
Dan.

1334
01:42:04,252 --> 01:42:05,819
Thanks.

1335
01:42:05,821 --> 01:42:06,987
Move!

1336
01:42:06,989 --> 01:42:08,255
[GUNSHOTS]

1337
01:42:31,295 --> 01:42:32,229
Come on!

1338
01:42:34,883 --> 01:42:37,167
Might not get a chance to use
those Scofields, Charlie.

1339
01:42:39,270 --> 01:42:40,688
Perhaps you
can explain to me

1340
01:42:40,690 --> 01:42:42,256
the next portion
of your plan, Dan.

1341
01:43:00,275 --> 01:43:01,691
MAN: 
I think I got him!

1342
01:43:06,998 --> 01:43:08,064
Hey.

1343
01:43:08,066 --> 01:43:09,366
Hey!

1344
01:43:09,368 --> 01:43:11,334
Not the black hat!

1345
01:43:11,336 --> 01:43:12,870
The rancher,
you dumb-shits!

1346
01:43:12,872 --> 01:43:15,522
The rancher!
The ranch--

1347
01:43:27,135 --> 01:43:28,452
Charlie!

1348
01:43:31,339 --> 01:43:33,007
Get back!
Get back! Get back!

1349
01:43:39,881 --> 01:43:41,281
Boss.

1350
01:43:41,283 --> 01:43:42,349
Boss!

1351
01:43:45,603 --> 01:43:47,237
Let's go.

1352
01:43:47,239 --> 01:43:48,572
The white door.
Move it!

1353
01:43:54,045 --> 01:43:55,179
[HORSE NEIGHS]

1354
01:44:09,727 --> 01:44:10,911
All right.

1355
01:44:12,580 --> 01:44:14,048
I ain't doing this
no more, Dan.

1356
01:44:14,050 --> 01:44:15,599
[DOOR OPENS]

1357
01:44:18,787 --> 01:44:20,421
I'm getting you
on that train, Wade.

1358
01:44:20,423 --> 01:44:22,556
Your son went back!

1359
01:44:22,558 --> 01:44:24,241
The boy's gone, hero.

1360
01:44:24,243 --> 01:44:26,743
Ain't nobody watching
no more.

1361
01:44:26,745 --> 01:44:28,011
You still got
that one good leg.

1362
01:44:28,013 --> 01:44:30,613
Why don't you use it
to get on home?

1363
01:44:30,615 --> 01:44:33,016
Charlie!

1364
01:44:33,018 --> 01:44:34,852
Charlie Prince!

1365
01:44:34,854 --> 01:44:35,953
Yeah, Boss!

1366
01:44:35,955 --> 01:44:37,454
Hold your fire.

1367
01:44:37,456 --> 01:44:39,589
I'm walking out.
CHARLIE: Hold your fire!

1368
01:45:04,516 --> 01:45:07,283
I ain't never been
no hero, Wade.

1369
01:45:09,471 --> 01:45:11,355
The only battle I seen,

1370
01:45:11,357 --> 01:45:13,274
we was in retreat.

1371
01:45:13,276 --> 01:45:15,643
My foot got shot off
by one of my own men.

1372
01:45:17,712 --> 01:45:21,348
You try telling
that story to your boy.

1373
01:45:21,350 --> 01:45:23,484
See how he looks
at you then.

1374
01:45:37,481 --> 01:45:40,601
CHARLIE:
Boss! Boss!

1375
01:45:44,405 --> 01:45:45,473
Okay, Dan.

1376
01:45:56,434 --> 01:45:57,768
Son.

1377
01:46:00,572 --> 01:46:02,022
They're on the roofs!

1378
01:46:02,024 --> 01:46:03,557
They're on the roofs!

1379
01:46:04,976 --> 01:46:06,076
Boss!

1380
01:46:35,023 --> 01:46:37,157
Boss! Drop!

1381
01:46:41,963 --> 01:46:43,296
Can you make this?
Yeah.

1382
01:46:55,793 --> 01:46:56,994
Come on.

1383
01:46:56,996 --> 01:46:58,862
Come on!

1384
01:47:17,848 --> 01:47:19,933
Go! Run!

1385
01:47:48,847 --> 01:47:49,797
Spread out!

1386
01:47:49,799 --> 01:47:50,731
[GUNSHOTS]

1387
01:48:02,476 --> 01:48:03,643
What time is it?

1388
01:48:05,180 --> 01:48:06,847
About 10 past 3.

1389
01:48:06,849 --> 01:48:08,882
Where's the 3:10
to Yuma?

1390
01:48:08,884 --> 01:48:10,284
Running late,
I suppose.

1391
01:48:10,286 --> 01:48:12,286
How late?
[GLASS SHATTERING]

1392
01:48:12,288 --> 01:48:13,720
Beats me.

1393
01:48:13,722 --> 01:48:15,189
Gets here
when it gets here.

1394
01:48:15,191 --> 01:48:17,891
Goddamn trains.
Never can rely on 'em, huh?

1395
01:48:26,134 --> 01:48:27,801
MAN: 
By the window!

1396
01:48:33,541 --> 01:48:35,008
[MOOING]

1397
01:48:36,644 --> 01:48:39,012
[GUNSHOTS]

1398
01:48:57,198 --> 01:48:58,498
You know...

1399
01:48:58,500 --> 01:49:00,667
[PANTING]

1400
01:49:00,669 --> 01:49:02,468
I ain't stubborn.

1401
01:49:04,122 --> 01:49:05,456
Excuse me?

1402
01:49:06,758 --> 01:49:08,859
You said I was stubborn

1403
01:49:08,861 --> 01:49:10,961
for keeping my family
on a dying ranch.

1404
01:49:13,114 --> 01:49:15,382
It's my son Mark.

1405
01:49:15,384 --> 01:49:17,484
The young one?

1406
01:49:17,486 --> 01:49:21,304
He got tuberculosis
when we was 2.

1407
01:49:21,306 --> 01:49:23,439
The doctor said he'd die

1408
01:49:23,441 --> 01:49:25,608
if he didn't
have a dry climate, so--

1409
01:49:25,610 --> 01:49:27,144
Why are you telling me this?

1410
01:49:29,280 --> 01:49:31,231
I don't know.

1411
01:49:31,233 --> 01:49:33,483
I guess I just...

1412
01:49:33,485 --> 01:49:38,522
wanted you to know
that I ain't stubborn is all.

1413
01:49:52,486 --> 01:49:53,936
[CATTLE MOOING]

1414
01:50:13,307 --> 01:50:14,808
WADE: Well,

1415
01:50:14,810 --> 01:50:16,676
as long as we're
making confessions--

1416
01:50:16,678 --> 01:50:18,295
DAN:
Yeah?

1417
01:50:18,297 --> 01:50:20,213
I've been
to Yuma Prison before.

1418
01:50:22,734 --> 01:50:24,150
Twice.

1419
01:50:24,152 --> 01:50:25,736
Escaped twice, too.

1420
01:50:27,388 --> 01:50:29,306
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

1421
01:50:43,838 --> 01:50:45,872
[BELL TOLLING]

1422
01:51:31,736 --> 01:51:34,037
First car, sliding door.

1423
01:51:46,100 --> 01:51:47,917
They'll be coming!

1424
01:52:05,853 --> 01:52:07,003
Hyah!

1425
01:52:08,872 --> 01:52:10,440
Hyah! Hyah!

1426
01:52:10,442 --> 01:52:11,624
Yeah.

1427
01:52:27,475 --> 01:52:29,476
I got a prisoner
to go to Yuma!

1428
01:52:36,133 --> 01:52:37,984
Well, you did it, Dan.

1429
01:52:39,153 --> 01:52:40,671
No!

1430
01:52:40,673 --> 01:52:41,754
[GUNSHOTS]

1431
01:52:51,615 --> 01:52:53,449
Pa.

1432
01:53:20,777 --> 01:53:23,813
For a one-leg rancher...

1433
01:53:26,617 --> 01:53:30,186
he's one tough son of a bitch.

1434
01:53:31,355 --> 01:53:32,622
Yeah.

1435
01:54:36,270 --> 01:54:37,770
You done it, Pa.

1436
01:54:40,624 --> 01:54:42,058
You done it.

1437
01:54:44,428 --> 01:54:46,563
You got him on the train.

1438
01:55:42,903 --> 01:55:44,537
Pa.

1439
01:56:12,933 --> 01:56:14,300
[TRAIN WHISTLE TOOTS]

1440
01:56:46,984 --> 01:56:48,184
[WHISTLES]